INSERT INTO `beers` VALUES (1,'Buzz','A Real Bitter Experience.','09/2007','A light, crisp and bitter IPA brewed with English and American hops. A small batch brewed only once.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.5,60,1010,1044,20,10,4.4,75,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-09-01'),(2,'Trashy Blonde','You Know You Shouldn\'t','04/2008','A titillating, neurotic, peroxide punk of a Pale Ale. Combining attitude, style, substance, and a little bit of low self esteem for good measure; what would your mother say? The seductive lure of the sassy passion fruit hop proves too much to resist. All that is even before we get onto the fact that there are no additives, preservatives, pasteurization or strings attached. All wrapped up with the customary BrewDog bite and imaginative twist.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/2.png',4.1,41.5,1010,1041.7,15,15,4.4,76,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-04-01'),(3,'Berliner Weisse With Yuzu - B-Sides','Japanese Citrus Berliner Weisse.','11/2015','Japanese citrus fruit intensifies the sour nature of this German classic.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.2,8,1007,1040,8,4,3.2,83,20,25,21,'Soured naturally using the kettle souring technique, Yuzu fruit: 50g at middle, Yuzu juice: 200ml at FV','Soured naturally using the kettle souring technique, Yuzu fruit: 50g at middle, Yuzu juice: 200ml at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-11-01'),(4,'Pilsen Lager','Unleash the Yeast Series.','09/2013','Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and Flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit Flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Pilsner yeast ferments with no fruity esters or spicy phenols, although it can add a hint of butterscotch.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/4.png',6.3,55,1012,1060,30,15,4.4,80,20,25,9,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',2,'2013-09-01'),(5,'Avery Brown Dredge','Bloggers\' Imperial Pilsner.','02/2011','An Imperial Pilsner in collaboration with beer writers. Tradition. Homage. Revolution. We wanted to showcase the awesome backbone of the Czech brewing tradition, the noble Saaz hop, and also tip our hats to the modern beers that rock our world, and the people who make them.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/5.png',7.2,59,1027,1069,10,5,4.4,67,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2011-02-01'),(6,'Electric India','Vibrant Hoppy Saison.','05/2013','Re-brewed as a spring seasonal, this beer – which appeared originally as an Equity Punk shareholder creation – retains its trademark spicy, fruity edge. A perfect blend of Belgian Saison and US IPA, crushed peppercorns and heather honey are also added to produce a genuinely unique beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/6.png',5.2,38,1005,1045,15,7.5,4.4,88.9,20,25,22,'Honey: 62.5g at End (WP), Coriander Seeds: 8.5g at 45mins','Honey: 62.5g at End (WP), Coriander Seeds: 8.5g at 45mins','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2013-05-01'),(7,'AB:12','Imperial Black Belgian Ale.','07/2012','An Imperial Black Belgian Ale aged in old Invergordon Scotch whisky barrels with mountains of raspberries, tayberries and blackberries in each cask. Decadent but light and dry, this beer would make a fantastic base for ageing on pretty much any dark fruit - we used raspberries, tayberries and blackberries beause they were local.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/7.png',11.2,35,1017,1108,80,40,5.3,84,20,25,21,'Aged in whisky barrels with raspberries, tayberries and blackberries','Aged in whisky barrels with raspberries, tayberries and blackberries','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2012-07-01'),(8,'Fake Lager','Bohemian Pilsner.','03/2013','Fake is the new black. Fake is where it is at. Fake Art, fake brands, fake breasts, and fake lager. We want to play our part in the ugly fallout from the Lager Dream. Say hello to Fake Lager – a zesty, floral 21st century faux masterpiece with added BrewDog bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/8.png',4.7,40,1010,1046,12,6,4.4,78,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2013-03-01'),(9,'AB:07','Whisky Cask-Aged Scotch Ale.','03/2010','Whisky cask-aged imperial scotch ale. Beer perfect for when the rain is coming sideways. Liquorice, plum and raisin temper the warming alcohol, producing a beer capable of holding back the Scottish chill.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/9.png',12.5,30,1020,1106,84,42,5.6,83,20,25,11,'Scottish Heather Honey: 62.5g at middle, Add honey during the boil. After fermentation, age in a Scottish whisky cask','Scottish Heather Honey: 62.5g at middle, Add honey during the boil. After fermentation, age in a Scottish whisky cask','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',5,'2010-03-01'),(10,'Bramling X','Single Hop IPA Series - 2011.','01/2011','Good old Bramling Cross is elegant, refined, assured, (boring) and understated. Understated that is unless you hop the living daylights out of a beer with it. This is Bramling Cross re-invented and re-imagined, and shows just what can be done with English hops if you use enough of them. Poor Bramling Cross normally gets lost in a woeful stream of conformist brown ales made by sleepy cask ale brewers. But not anymore. This beer shows that British hops do have some soul, and is a fruity riot of blackberries, pears, and plums. Reminds me of the bramble, apple and ginger jam my grandmother used to make.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/10.png',7.5,75,1013,1068,22,11,4.4,80.9,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2011-01-01'),(11,'Misspent Youth','Milk & Honey Scotch Ale.','04/2013','The brainchild of our small batch brewer, George Woods. A dangerously drinkable milk sugar- infused Scotch Ale.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.3,30,1020,1079,120,60,4.4,74.7,20,25,19,'See honey and lactose additions','See honey and lactose additions','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-04-01'),(12,'Arcade Nation','Seasonal Black IPA.','12/2015','Running the knife-edge between an India Pale Ale and a Stout, this particular style is one we truly love. Black IPAs are a great showcase for the skill of our brew team, balancing so many complex and twisting Flavours in the same moment. The citrus, mango and pine from the hops – three of our all-time favourites – play off against the roasty dryness from the malt bill at each and every turn.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/12.png',5.3,60,1012,1052,200,100,4.2,77,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-12-01'),(13,'Movember','Moustache-Worthy Beer.','11/2009','A deliciously robust, black malted beer with a decadent dark, dry cocoa Flavour that provides an enticing backdrop to the Cascade hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/13.png',4.5,50,1012,1047,140,70,5.2,74.5,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2009-11-01'),(14,'Alpha Dog','Existential Red Ale.','02/2010','A fusion of caramel malt Flavours and punchy New Zealand hops. A session beer you can get your teeth into.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/14.png',4.5,42,1025,1046,62,31,4.4,72.8,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2010-02-01'),(15,'Mixtape 8','An Epic Fusion Of Old Belgian, American New Wave, And Scotch Whisky.','01/2012','This recipe is for the Belgian Tripel base. A blend of two huge oak aged beers – half a hopped up Belgian Tripel, and half a Triple India Pale Ale. Both aged in single grain whisky barrels for two years and blended, each beer brings its own character to the mix. The Belgian Tripel comes loaded with complex spicy, fruity esters, and punchy citrus hop character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/15.png',14.5,50,1014,1093,40,20,4.4,85,20,25,21,'Barrel aged and blended with Anarchist Alchemist','Barrel aged and blended with Anarchist Alchemist','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2012-01-01'),(16,'Libertine Porter','Dry-Hopped Aggressive Porter.','01/2012','An avalanche of cross-continental hop varieties give this porter a complex spicy, resinous and citrusy aroma, with a huge malt bill providing a complex roasty counterpoint. Digging deeper into the Flavour draws out cinder toffee, bitter chocolate and hints of woodsmoke.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/16.png',6.1,45,1020,1067,219,109.5,4.4,70.1,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-01-01'),(17,'AB:06','Imperial Black IPA.','04/2011','Our sixth Abstrakt, this imperial black IPA combined dark malts with a monumental triple dry-hop, using an all-star team of some of our favourite American hops. Roasty and resinous.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/17.png',11.2,150,1013,1098,70,35,NULL,87,20,25,17,'White cane sugar: 150g at middle','White cane sugar: 150g at middle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-04-01'),(18,'Russian Doll – India Pale Ale','Nesting Hop Bomb.','08/2014','The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected Flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/18.png',6,70,1012,1058,25,12.5,5.2,79.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-08-01'),(19,'Hello My Name Is Mette-Marit','Lingonberry Double IPA.','06/2013','We sent this beer to Norway where it was known as \'Hello, my name is Censored’. You can make up your own mind as to why. This brew was a red berry explosion, with a reisnous bitter edge layered with dry berry tartness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/19.png',8.2,70,1013,1076,NULL,NULL,4.4,83,20,25,19,'Infusion of lingonberries alongside the dry hops, Cranberry Juice: 5.5g at 30mins, Lingonberries: 10g Twist','Infusion of lingonberries alongside the dry hops, Cranberry Juice: 5.5g at 30mins, Lingonberries: 10g Twist','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-06-01'),(20,'Rabiator','Imperial Wheat Beer','03/2011','Imperial Wheat beer / Weizenbock brewed by a homesick German in leather trousers. Think banana bread, bubble gum and David Hasselhoff.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',10.27,26,1014,1092,24,12,4.4,85,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',7,'2011-03-01'),(21,'Vice Bier','Hoppy Wheat Bier.','04/2013','Our take on the classic German Kristallweizen. A clear German wheat beer, layers of bubblegum and vanilla perfectly balanced with the American and New Zealand hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.3,25,1010,1043,30,15,4,81.8,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',8,'2013-04-01'),(22,'Devine Rebel (w/ Mikkeller)','Oak-aged Barley Wine.','12/2008','Two of Europe\'s most experimental, boundary-pushing brewers, BrewDog and Mikkeller, combined forces to produce a rebellious beer that combined their respective talents and brewing skills. The 12.5% Barley Wine fermented well, and the champagne yeast drew it ever closer to 12.5%. The beer was brewed with a single hop variety and was going to be partially aged in oak casks.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/22.png',12.5,100,1030,1093,36,18,4.4,68,20,25,19,'Part-aged in oak barrels, finished with champagne yeast','Part-aged in oak barrels, finished with champagne yeast','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-12-01'),(23,'Storm','Islay Whisky Aged IPA.','12/2007','Dark and powerful Islay magic infuses this tropical sensation of an IPA. Using the original Punk IPA as a base, we boosted the ABV to 8% giving it some extra backbone to stand up to the peated smoke imported directly from Islay.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/23.png',8,60,1010,1082,12,6,4.4,86,20,25,19,'Oak chips soaked in Islay whisky 50g','Oak chips soaked in Islay whisky 50g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-12-01'),(24,'The End Of History','The World\'s Strongest Beer.','06/2011','The End of History: The name derives from the famous work of philosopher Francis Fukuyama, this is to beer what democracy is to history. Complexity defined. Floral, grapefruit, caramel and cloves are intensified by boozy heat.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/24.png',55,NULL,1000,1112,NULL,NULL,4.4,100,20,25,20,'Nettles: 25g at end, Juniper: 25g at end','Nettles: 25g at end, Juniper: 25g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2011-06-01'),(25,'Bad Pixie','Spiced Wheat Beer.','10/2008','2008 Prototype beer, a 4.7% wheat ale with crushed juniper berries and citrus peel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/25.png',4.7,45,1010,1047,8,4,4.4,79,20,25,19,'Crushed juniper berries: 12.5g, Lemon peel: 18.8g','Crushed juniper berries: 12.5g, Lemon peel: 18.8g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-10-01'),(26,'Skull Candy','Pacific Hopped Amber Bitter.','02/2010','The first beer that we brewed on our newly commissioned 5000 litre brewhouse in Fraserburgh 2009. A beer with the malt and body of an English bitter, but the heart and soul of vibrant citrus US hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.5,33,1012,1038,50,25,4.4,68.4,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2010-02-01'),(27,'Dog B','Cacao, Coffee Chili Anniversary Stout.','05/2013','Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn\'t change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental Stout.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/27.png',15,90,1003,1120,100,50,4.4,98,20,25,19,'Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.','Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-05-01'),(28,'HBC 369','Single Hop India Pale Ale – 2012.','02/2012','HBC 369 brings rich fruity Flavours with the tiniest layer of candy coating on top. HBC 369 (the hop) can bring notes of blueberries, pear, and possibly even sweet potato. HBC 369 (the beer) was balanced, with just one hop providing a complex aroma, and a dry bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/28.png',6.7,67,1064,1013,19,9.5,4.4,79.7,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-02-01'),(29,'10 Heads High','Imperial Red Ale.','04/2013','10 Heads High is loosely based on our awesome 2011 Prototype beer Hops Kill Nazis. This is an uncompromising 7.8% Imperial Red Ale loaded high with American Hops. Think of this as an Imperial India Red Ale, or a super-charged version of 5am Saint. Either way this is a seriously good beer!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/29.png',7.8,70,1015,1074,90,45,4.4,79.7,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2013-04-01'),(30,'Dana - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2013','Hailing from Slovenia, Dana was originally cross bred from the German Hallertau Magnum and native Slovenian varieties. Like any good faux noble hop should, it infuses a rustic, musty spiciness into a toasty beast of a malt base.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/30.png',6.7,70,1015,1066,30,15,4.4,77.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2013-02-01'),(31,'Nanny State','Alcohol Free Hoppy Ale.','08/2009','Brewing a full Flavoured craft beer at 0.5% is no easy task. Packed with loads of Centennial, Amarillo, Columbus, Cascade and Simcoe hops, dry hopped to the brink and back and sitting at 55 IBUs, Nanny State is a force to be reckoned with. With a backbone of 8 different specialty malts, Nanny State will tantalise your taste buds and leave you yearning for more.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/31.png',0.5,55,1005,1007,30,15,4.4,28.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2009-08-01'),(32,'AB:05','Belgian Imperial Stout.','12/2010','Belgian Imperial Stout aged on toasted coconut and cacao. The Belgian yeast strain introduces a whole new dimension to the Imperial Stout style resulting in a beer that resembles a marshmallow toasted on a smouldering barbeque then smothered in dark chocolate. Massively seductive and encapsulating this blacker than midnight beer pours with coffee brown head so thick you could almost stand on it, and with an epic lacing on your glass.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/32.png',12.5,40,1030,1126,180,90,4.4,76,20,25,19,'Toasted coconut flakes: 75g, Cacao Nibs: 25g','Toasted coconut flakes: 75g, Cacao Nibs: 25g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2010-12-01'),(33,'Sorachi Ace','Single Hop IPA Series - 2011.','01/2011','A hop that tastes of bubble gum? Seriously? No, we did not believe it either. But it does! This is one unique, son of a bitch of a hop. Lemony, deep, musty with a smoothness that belies its power. This hop is lemony like a lemon who was angry earlier but is now tired because of all the rage. This hop of Japanese origin is best enjoyed trying to make sushi from your gold fish, or trying to persuade your girlfriend (or boyfriend maybe) to dress up as a Geisha for Valentine’s Day.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/33.png',7.5,75,1013,1068,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2011-01-01'),(34,'Bourbon Baby','Barrel-Aged Scotch Ale.','01/2014','Santa Paws Scotch ale aged in bourbon barrels - light, dry and toasty, with vanilla, hints of chocolate and ginger biscuit, and a faint spicy hoppiness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/34.png',5.8,35,1005,1049,44,22,4.4,90,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2014-01-01'),(35,'Berliner Weisse With Raspberries And Rhubarb - B-Sides','Fruity Berliner Weisse.','11/2015','Tart, dry and acidic with a punch of summer berry as rhubarb crumble.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.6,8,1007,1040,NULL,NULL,3.2,83,20,25,21,'Raspberries in the boil, rhubarb at maturation. Soured naturally using the kettle souring technique, Raspberries at middle','Raspberries in the boil, rhubarb at maturation. Soured naturally using the kettle souring technique, Raspberries at middle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-11-01'),(36,'Shipwrecker Circus (w/ Oskar Blues)','American Barley Wine - Oskar Blues Collab.','09/2013','In collaboration with the awesome Oskar Blues from Colorado, we created this big, twisted 10.5% American style barley wine. Big boozy aromas and a sweet viscosity, packed in with some heavy-hitting C-hops, for an intense bitterness to balance this full-bodied malt monster.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/36.png',10.5,85,1022,1102,64,32,4.4,102,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',6,'2013-09-01'),(37,'Zephyr','There’s A Storm Brewing.','10/2008','A 9.2% Double IPA aged for 21 months in a 1965 Invergordon cask with 30 kg of fresh highland strawberries. This beer is a riot of whisky, caramel and strawberry, all tempered by a toe curling bitterness enducing rapture in all who taste it. Who needs champagne?','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/37.png',12.5,125,1016,1087,40,20,4.4,81.2,20,25,21,'Oak chips: 15g, Fresh strawberries: 3kg','Oak chips: 15g, Fresh strawberries: 3kg','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2008-10-01'),(38,'Belgian Trappist','Unleash the Yeast Series.','09/2013','Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and Flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit Flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Abbey style yeasts add distinctive spicy and fruity notes, and dry out the finished beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/38.png',6.3,55,1012,1060,30,15,4.4,80,20,25,25,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',9,'2013-09-01'),(39,'Kohatu - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2014','As you’d expect from a New Zealand hop variety, Kohatu contributes bags of tropical fruit, but with loads of lime notes, & pineapple hits. Seriously fruity, with sweet, juicy melon and stonefruit notes.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/39.png',7.2,70,1012,1067,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-02-01'),(40,'Hello My Name is Vladimir','Limonnik Infused Imperial IPA (Not for Gays).','01/2014','A Limonnik-infused, triple dry- hopped double IPA. Dry berry tartness and intense citrus hop character meld with a dry bready malt base, boosted by a hint of alcohol warmth. This beer was brewed as a protest against the anti-LGBT legislation in Russia surrounding the Sochi Olympics.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/40.png',8.2,70,1013,1076,16,8,4.4,83,20,25,21,'Fruit in the boil, berries in the fermenter. Limonnik Berries: 2.5, Twist.','Fruit in the boil, berries in the fermenter. Limonnik Berries: 2.5, Twist.','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2014-01-01'),(41,'AB:17','Three Coffee Rye Imperial Porter.','10/2014','A triple whammy of coffee from HasBean gives our 17th Abstrakt concept beer an intense and roasty, dark mocha character. We brewed with espresso in the mash, cafetiere in the boil, and whole roast beans in the whirlpool and the fermenter.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/41.png',10.7,100,1025,1105,300,150,4.3,76.2,20,25,21,'Coffee: 25g at end, Coffee: 25g at end, Dark Muscavado Sugar: 250g at end','Coffee: 25g at end, Coffee: 25g at end, Dark Muscavado Sugar: 250g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-10-01'),(42,'Hardcore IPA','Explicit Imperial Ale. Citrusy. Resinous. Intense.','12/2009','Pounding a triple payload of the biggest North American hops humanity has devised, braced by a backbone of caramel malt, this beer is deep, astringent and resinous, pushing to the extremes of lupulin thresholds. There’s nothing inscrutable going on; no mystery in the backstory. It doesn’t seek to be understood. A beer incapable of empathy; only hop overload.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/42.png',9.2,125,1016,1085,40,20,4.4,81.2,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2009-12-01'),(43,'American Wheat','Hoppy American Wheat.','07/2014','A luscious blend of peach, blood orange and banana to make a suitably refreshing beverage that happily straddles the Atlantic.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.5,17,1013,1047,10,5,5.3,72,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',10,'2014-07-01'),(44,'Dog Wired (w/8 Wired)','New Zealand Imperial Pilsner.','06/2013','Brewed in collaboration with Soren from New Zealand’s stellar 8-Wired brewery, this is an Imperial Pilsner featuring two of our favourite New Zealand hops: Nelson Sauvin and Motueka. Sitting at a dangerously drinkable 7.1% ABV there’s a touch of Munich malt which gives this beer that little extra caramel biscuit bite to compliment the lip smackingly tropical hops. Expect an all out NZ hoppy riot.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/44.png',7.1,65,1010,1065,13,6.5,4.4,85,20,25,9,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2013-06-01'),(45,'The Physics','Laid Back Amber Beer.','04/2007','A hoppy Amber Ale that won World\'s Best Amber Beer in the World Beer Awards 2007. Malt and hops are in perfect harmony in this incredibly balanced beer. Biscuity, bitter and packing a surprisingly hoppy punch, this beer ultimately morphed into 5AM Saint.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/45.png',5,47,1010,1048.5,65,32.5,4.4,79.4,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-04-01'),(46,'Anarchist Alchemist','Triple Hopped Triple Ipa.','03/2012','About as far as you can push an IPA; Anarchist Alchemist packs in three times the malt and three of our favourite hops. Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo and Centennial bring a range of Flavours, touching on tropical fruit, white grape, tangerine, grapefruit, pine, spiced orange... the list goes on!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/46.png',16.5,20.5,1000,1112,20,10,4.4,100,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-03-01'),(47,'AB:15','Salted Caramel Popcorn Strong Ale.','03/2013','A salted caramel popcorn Imperial Ale. Bourbon and Rum barrel aged, this 12.8% ale has complex and twisting Flavours. Bitter caramel, wood, smoke, spice, treacle and vanilla are all present and intertwine against a smooth and lightly chewy mouthfeel. The salted caramel popcorn lends subtle hints of a smoky brininess.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/47.png',12.8,50,1020,1096,111,55.5,4.4,79.17,20,25,21,'Adding popped popcorn into the mash, then barrel ageing in fresh bourbon barrels','Adding popped popcorn into the mash, then barrel ageing in fresh bourbon barrels','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2013-03-01'),(48,'Goldings - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2013','This is East Kent Goldings re- invented and re-imagined and shows just what can be done with English hops if you use enough of them. In this amped up Goldings reincarnation expect to be slammed with floral lavender, a fruity riot of blackberries and spiced pears, bubblegum, plums and the illusion of thyme.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/48.png',6.7,70,1015,1066,30,15,4.4,77.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2013-02-01'),(49,'AB:14','Oak-Aged Imperial Weizenbock.','02/2013','Think banoffee pie; loads of creamy sweet banana, and sticky warm toffee. This beer is super complex, and one for the sweet-toothed!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/49.png',10,30,1016,1094,20,10,4.4,83,20,25,23,'Oak chips: 25g at end','Oak chips: 25g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',8,'2013-02-01'),(50,'Lost Dog (w/Lost Abbey)','Rum-Aged Imperial Porter - Lost Abbey Collab.','11/2011','Our first beer aged in rum casks, Lost Dog saw us brew a collaboration imperial porter with our friends at Lost Abbey. The base beer was packed with toffee, chocolate and roasty notes, balanced with a subtle spicy hop character. The rum casks add a warming, spiced vanilla edge.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/50.png',10,35,1012,1080,80,40,4.4,85,20,25,19,'Aged in rum casks for 12 months','Aged in rum casks for 12 months','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-11-01'),(51,'TM10','Liquid Art.','04/2010','Brewed for the Tate Modern’s 10th Anniversary. A saison style beer brewed with ginger and orange peel. Very limited batch of 4000 cork and caged bottles with a silk screened label designed by Johanna Basford. Only available at the Tate Modern.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/51.png',5.5,20,1005,1048,14,7,4.2,89.6,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2010-04-01'),(52,'Paradox Islay','Ubiquitous Imperial Stout.','04/2007','In 2006 James and Martin hijacked a beer dinner run by Michael Jackson, the acclaimed beer and whisky writer, and convinced him to taste one of their home brews. This was a defining moment in BrewDog prehistory, and that beer was the first incarnation of the ubiquitous Paradox. Aged in a variety of casks over the years, Paradox is dark, decadent and encapsulating. Can be enjoyed fresh; phenomenal when aged.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/52.png',10,55,1014,1090,300,152,4.4,84.4,20,25,21,'Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2007-04-01'),(53,'Baby Dogma','Session Scotch Ale.','09/2013','A baby Scotch ale with dry and toasty malt Flavours and hints of smoke. Toffee, biscuit and fudge abound with a spicy bitterness from the pan-global hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.5,35,1013,1048,40,20,4.4,72.9,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-09-01'),(54,'Albino Squid Assasin','Red Rye IPA','11/2015','This tentacled terminator packs a punch - ten punches to be precise. Each hop addition adds to the intense layers of depth in this red rye IPA. Toasty caramel & cinder toffee from crystal malts, cacao richness from intensely roasted malt and the spiciness of rye. Zesty pithiness from Citra and the robust resin of Chinook. This small batch exclusive brew is up-front intensity matched with twisted complexity. The can features awesome custom art from Joe Wilson.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/54.png',7.4,65,1012,1069,60,30,4.2,82.6,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2015-11-01'),(55,'Amarillo - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','01/2013','Citrus fruit. Lots of citrus fruit. Think blood orange, orange zest and grapefruit, tangerine and lemon; the fruit is balanced by floral notes in the most classic of new wave IPA hops. Amarillo adds a zesty, pithy character that sits beautifully alongside hints of toffee and honeycomb.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/55.png',7.2,70,1012,1067,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-01-01'),(56,'Black Eyed King Imp','Barrel-Aged Prototype Cocoa Psycho.','11/2012','An early Cocoa Psycho recipe that we loved, but didn\'t fit what we were looking for. We locked this chocolate coffee stout away in barrels for two years, imparting toasted marshmallow, spicy vanilla, molasses and boozy warmth.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/56.png',9.5,85,1022,1095,250,125,4.4,76.8,20,25,18,'Coffee Beans: 12.5g at end, Lactose: 125g','Coffee Beans: 12.5g at end, Lactose: 125g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-11-01'),(57,'Prototype 27','Vibrant Smoky Pink IPA.','04/2010','Hardcore IPA with raspberries aged in Caol Ila casks. Full-bodied and compelling, the robust malt base provides an initial layer of honey, cinnamon and biscuity malt sweetness. Soon the Scottish berries are in on the act, a dominating tug of war between sweet and tart with an overbearing zest. As the beer slips back across your tongue the hops demand and definitely get your attention. At 100 IBUs the bitterness smashes into the back of your throat as the resinous, spiced orange peel Flavours add depth to the berry fruitiness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/57.png',9.2,149,1014,1083,19.5,9.8,4.4,83,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-04-01'),(58,'Coffee Imperial Stout','Beats a Cup of Joe.','11/2008','This beer was released as both as \"Danish Beerhouse Coffee Imperial Stout\" and \"BrewDog Coffee Imperial Stout\". Deep, dark, roasted Flavours make this a perfect Sunday brunch beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/58.png',9,65,1019,1080,97,49,4.4,76,20,25,19,'Coffee added after boil. Aged on French oak chips., Dark muscovado sugar: 312.5g for 20mins','Coffee added after boil. Aged on French oak chips., Dark muscovado sugar: 312.5g for 20mins','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-11-01'),(59,'Mandarina Bavaria - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','03/2015','From the central European plains of Germany, comes something very different. A blast of tangerine and orange, Mandarina Bavaria brings a highly distinctive backbone of Flavour. This is down to its parent – Cascade – and a frankly enormous 70% myrcene oil content. If equate Germany solely with earthy, spicy Noble hops, Mandarina Bavaria will make you think again.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/59.png',7.2,100,1010,1064,12,6,4.4,84,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(60,'Dogma','Revamped Wee Heavy. Luscious. Malty. Fruity.','07/2013','Brewed with over ten different types of malt, and blended together with Scottish heather honey, it is a pantheon to the gods of intricacy and nuance; a beer that celebratesa confluence of ideas. Complex, indulgent and encapsulating, Dogma gives more than a cursory nod to history, to make you ponder the very nature of beer itself.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/60.png',7.5,30,1023,1080,46,23,4.5,70,20,25,12,'Heather Honey: 125g','Heather Honey: 125g','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',2,'2013-07-01'),(61,'Magic Stone Dog (w/Magic Rock & Stone Brewing Co.)','Session Farmhouse IPA - Stone / Magic Rock Collab.','06/2014','A session IPA brewed with a diverse grain bill, hopped with Simcoe and Amarillo and fermented with saison yeast, for an incredible level of depth in a low ABV beer. Spicy, fruity, complex, refreshing and dry.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/61.png',4.6,30,1008,1043,15,7.5,4.4,81.4,20,25,23,'Cumin: 0.5g at end, Caraway: 1g at end, Peppercorns (Pink): 5g at end, Grains of Paradise: 5g at end','Cumin: 0.5g at end, Caraway: 1g at end, Peppercorns (Pink): 5g at end, Grains of Paradise: 5g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2014-06-01'),(62,'AB:08','Deconstructed Blonde Imperial Stout.','11/2011','Flavours and aromas you\'d expect from a Stout, but brewed without dark malts. The full mouthfeel comes courtesy of wheat and oats, while smoked malt and the twist additions add the complex Flavours normally provided by highly kilned malts.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/62.png',10.43,65,1016,1095,23,11.5,4.4,83.2,20,25,21,'Cacao: 25g at FV, Coffee Beans: 37.5g at FV, Oak Chips: 5g at FV, Vanilla Pods: 10 split pods, Liquorice: 5g at FV','Cacao: 25g at FV, Coffee Beans: 37.5g at FV, Oak Chips: 5g at FV, Vanilla Pods: 10 split pods, Liquorice: 5g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-11-01'),(63,'Sunk Punk','Ocean Fermented Lager.','09/2011','It\'s rumoured just a drop can calm the fiercest of storms. A balance of sweet, salt and savoury, citrus, spruce and caramel. Fermented at the bottom of the North Sea, which just so happens to be the perfect temperature for lagers to ferment.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/63.png',7.1,68,1010,1056,14,7,4.4,82.1,20,25,10,'Seabuckthorn: 25g at end, Sea Salt: 20g at middle, Rum: 25ml at end','Seabuckthorn: 25g at end, Sea Salt: 20g at middle, Rum: 25ml at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2011-09-01'),(64,'Sub Hop','Hopped-Up Imperial Pilsner.','06/2014','Brewed for the opening of our first bar in Italy, BrewDog Firenze. A mega-hoppy Imperial Pilsner, with toasty malt complexity and tropical New World hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/64.png',8,35,1016,1077,15,7.5,4.4,79.2,20,25,9,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2014-06-01'),(65,'Bracken\'s Porter','A Tribute To Our Favourite 4 Pawed Friend.','03/2013','The beer was named Bracken’s Porter as a tribute to our favourite four pawed friend who sadly passed in 2013. Chocolately, robust, warming, laid back and lots of fun - there are plenty of similarities between the two. Bracken we miss you and we hope you like your beer. Long live the original BrewDog.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5,50,1010,1049,110,55,4.4,79,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-03-01'),(66,'Tokyo Rising Sun - Lowland','A Beautiful Accident.','06/2009','A forgotten gem in the deepest, darkest corner of the warehouse. Aged in a Lowland whisky cask resulting in decadent chocolate, toasted vanilla, indulgent spiced fruit, a mesmerizingly hypnotic mouthfeel and new layers that emerge on every sip.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/66.png',13.2,85,1023,1125,140,71,4.4,82.17,20,25,21,'Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at start, Oak chips soaked in lowland whisky: 15g at dry hop','Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at start, Oak chips soaked in lowland whisky: 15g at dry hop','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',11,'2009-06-01'),(67,'Hunter Foundation Pale Ale','American Pale Ale.','05/2012','This straight-up US style pale ale uses some of our favourite hops against a toasty malt base. We brewed this with Sir Tom Hunter at our Fraserburgh brewery - to add a charitable element to your own version, feel free to share this citrusy pale ale with your friends. Or don\'t, it\'s your choice.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/67.png',5.4,35,1008,1050,11.5,5.75,4.4,84,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-05-01'),(68,'Hype','New Zealand Pale Ale.','08/2007','A perfect pale ale showcase for the tropical profile of New Zealand hops and the intense citrus of US hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.1,65,1010,1042,17,8.5,4.4,76.2,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2007-08-01'),(69,'AB:16','Coffee-Infused Belgian Quad.','02/2014','On the nose, clove and nutmeg, cafe au lait, subtle dark fruit notes, and hints of candied lemon peel. On the palate, smooth & fruity espresso, milk chocolate, and warm brandy-soaked currants are in the middle of a high-class dance-off against the spicy and peppery Belgian character. The overall impression evokes malt loaf or ginger cake.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/69.png',10.6,55,1012,1090,30,15,4.4,86.7,20,25,21,'Coffee Beans: 250g FV. Raisins: 90g at end. Dark Sugar:140g at end.','Coffee Beans: 250g FV. Raisins: 90g at end. Dark Sugar:140g at end.','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',12,'2014-02-01'),(70,'Sunmaid Stout','Rum & Raisin Imperial Stout.','12/2011','Brewed by Chris Sartori from Stone Brewing Company in 2010. A dark chocolate stout with dried dark fruit finish. Simcoe provides bitterness with subtle fruity supporting notes, contrasting the chocolate and coffee-laden malt profile. The finish is warming with vanilla and rich dark fruit depth.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',10.2,50,1102,1026,197,100,4.4,74.5,20,25,21,'Age in whisky casks with rum soaked raisins','Age in whisky casks with rum soaked raisins','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-12-01'),(71,'Pale - Russian Doll','Nesting Hop Bomb.','08/2014','The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected Flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/71.png',4,35,1010,1041,45,22.5,5.2,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-08-01'),(72,'Whisky Sour - B-Sides','Pilot Brew - Deconstructed Whisky Sour.','03/2015','Deconstructed whisky sour, reconstructed as a beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7,20,1021,1081,12,6,3.2,74,20,25,NULL,'Kettle Soured','Kettle Soured','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-03-01'),(73,'Black Eyed King Imp - Vietnamese Coffee Edition','Vietnamese Coffee Edition.','12/2014','This is the Vietnamese Coffee Edition. At 12.7% ABV, Black Eyed King Imp is a super intense and twistedly complex brew, with intense notes of sweet vanilla, rich espresso, smooth molasses and bitter chocolate barely contained by the whatever container it\'s in.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/73.png',12.7,85,1038,1113.5,250,125,5.2,76.8,20,25,18,'Coffee Beans: 12.5g at end, Lactose: 125g at FV, Bourbon barrel aged','Coffee Beans: 12.5g at end, Lactose: 125g at FV, Bourbon barrel aged','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-12-01'),(74,'Eurotrash','Belgian Blonde.','10/2009','Trashy Blonde with a Belgian Twist. Clove oil, red apples and a drier mouthfeel set this beer apart from its older sister.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.1,52,1010,1041,17,8.5,5.2,76,20,25,19,'Fermented with Belgian yeast for signature character','Fermented with Belgian yeast for signature character','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2009-10-01'),(75,'Never Mind The Anabolics','Performance-Enhancing India Pale Ale.','06/2012','Never Mind the Anabolics, a 6.5% India Pale Ale brewed with copious amounts of performance-enhancing natural ingredients. Brewed to commemorate the 2012 Olympics and its merry marketing bandwagon.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/75.png',6.5,35,1012,1050,23,11.5,4.4,76,20,25,18,'Lycii Berries: 7.5g at end, Ginseng: 5.625g at end, Guarana: 25g at end, Kolabu: 25g at end, Gingko: 6.25g at end, Matcha Tea: 12.5g at end, Maca Powder: 16.25g at end','Lycii Berries: 7.5g at end, Ginseng: 5.625g at end, Guarana: 25g at end, Kolabu: 25g at end, Gingko: 6.25g at end, Matcha Tea: 12.5g at end, Maca Powder: 16.25g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-06-01'),(76,'#Mashtag 2013','Democratic American Brown Ale.','05/2013','A rich, nutty Brown Ale with a deep, rich malt profile, hopped with a range of citrusy and spicy US varieties. Mellow yet endlessly complex, with enough chocolate and fruit character to balance the bitterness, and a soft oaky roundness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/76.png',7.5,50,1013,1070,40,20,4.4,81.4,20,25,21,'Roasted Hazelnuts: 25g in Tank (FV), Almonds: 12.5g in Tank (FV), Oak Chips: 25g in Tank (FV)','Roasted Hazelnuts: 25g in Tank (FV), Almonds: 12.5g in Tank (FV), Oak Chips: 25g in Tank (FV)','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2013-05-01'),(77,'Hobo Pop','2013 Prototype Rye Pale Ale.','11/2013','Brewed with mountains of Wheat, Rye, Cara and Crystal malts, fermented with an American ale yeast and bittered with Amarillo & Centennial, this 4.2% beer is what happens if something classy like a European wheat beer goes to live in Vegas. Zingy citrus hops and a punchy bitterness bolster this low ABV pale.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/77.png',4.2,50,1010,1042,30,15,4.4,76.2,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-11-01'),(78,'AB:18','Imperial Brown Ale Aged In Rum Casks.','10/2011','AB:18 began life as an Imperial Brown Ale before we bombarded it with Scottish tayberries and Purple raspberries and locked it away in rum barrels for two years, infusing rich dark fruit Flavours and oaky warmth into the mix.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/78.png',11.8,80,1020,1096,115,57.5,5.2,79.2,20,25,20,'Age in rum barrels, Tayberries: 500g, Purple Raspberries: 500g','Age in rum barrels, Tayberries: 500g, Purple Raspberries: 500g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-10-01'),(79,'Hops Kill Nazis','Imperial Red Ale.','08/2011','5AM Saint\'s big brother. Dry- hopping with Chinook gave Hops Kill Nazis a full-on, instantly recognisable US hop character - huge resinous aromas (think giant redwood) with a bitter grapefruit edge. The caramel malts bring Flavours of toffee and burnt sugar, which gave Hops Kill Nazis a big, complex malt base supporting the intense hopping.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/79.png',7.6,70,1015,1073,59,29.5,4.4,79.5,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-08-01'),(80,'AB:04','Imperial Stout With Coffee, Loads Of Cocoa And Chilli.','08/2010','Imperial Stout brewed with coffee, cocoa, Naga chillies (the hottest in the world), and champagne yeast. Possibly our most acclaimed Abstrakt yet.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/80.png',15,80,1018,1113,400,200,4,84.1,20,25,21,'Add chillies, cacoa and naga chillies to the cold conditioning','Add chillies, cacoa and naga chillies to the cold conditioning','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-08-01'),(81,'India Session Lager - Prototype Challenge','Refreshing Hop Fix.','11/2015','BrewDog’s level of dry-hop to a beer formed with a baseline of 100% pilsner malt – and at under 4.5% ABV – gives you a style that flirts at the edges of several others. Think aromas of fresh cut grass, nettle, white grape, melon, tangerine - with similar Flavours leading to a dry, bitter finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.4,35,1007,1040,12,6,4.4,79.5,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2015-11-01'),(82,'Hopped-Up Brown Ale - Prototype Challenge','Malt Hop Balance.','01/2016','Brown ales are perfect foils for resinous C-Hops, as the piney elements of the latter contrast brilliantly with the sweeter, nutty elements of the malt bill. The best of both worlds.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/82.png',6.3,85,1015,1063,24,12,4.2,82.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2016-01-01'),(83,'Comet','Single Hop India Pale Ale','02/2014','A potently bitter hop variety originally grown in the US around 40 years ago, Comet has been newly resurrected - this German version has bold resinous grapefruit Flavours, which add a huge fresh hop aroma to this IPA.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/83.png',7.2,70,1012,1067,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2014-02-01'),(84,'Baby Saison - B-Sides','Trial Baby Saison.','08/2015','A hark back to the origins of Saison; slight spice and earthy notes with highlights of lemon and pepper make a beer that could quench the thirst of any seasonal worker.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.6,9,1004,1032,2,1,4.4,88,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',3,'2015-08-01'),(85,'Santa Paws','Christmas Scoth Ale.','10/2010','A 4.5% decadent scotch ale brewed with Scottish heather honey. A robust malty beer packed with Flavour, at a strength you can drink all (Christmas) day long. Santa Paws is our antidote to the chaos of the festive season. All the Flavours of Christmas pudding in liquid form.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/85.png',4.5,35,1013,1048,44,22,4.4,72.9,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2010-10-01'),(86,'Original Dogma (Née Speedball)','Strong Ale With Honey And Spices.','07/2008','A strong ale, brewed with guarana, Californian poppy, kola nut and Scottish heather honey. A conspiracy of trans-continental ingredients infused with some devastatingly BrewDog imaginative thinking.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/86.png',7.8,60,1012,1071.3,31,15.5,4.3,83.2,20,25,21,'Herb and honey addition','Herb and honey addition','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',13,'2008-07-01'),(87,'Alpha Pop','Hoppy Rye Pale Ale.','03/2014','A hoppy Rye Ale loaded with an avalanche of citrus and resinous Flavours. Columbus, our high-alpha friend, lends a huge pithy citrus blast, with Ahtanum providing a punchy tropical fruit back-up. Brewing with rye adds a spiciness to the speciality malt caramel backbone, giving a warm ginger snap Flavour, before slowly the hops, barley and rye combine and build to an orangey, biscuity, almost chocolatey crescendo.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/87.png',4.5,30,1011,1045,25,12.5,4.4,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-03-01'),(88,'Bavarian Weizen','Unleash the Yeast Series.','09/2013','Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and Flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit Flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Bavarian Weizen yeast adds traditional weissbier notes of banana and clove.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/88.png',6.3,55,1012,1060,30,15,4.4,80,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',14,'2013-09-01'),(89,'Citra','Single Hop IPA Series – 2011.','01/2011','The Pacific North West of America is home to the Citra hop. America is not just about cheer leaders, a silly version of football, elastic top jeans and cheeseburgers. They grow remarkable hops and Citra is a killer example of this, embodying all that is good about American hops and then some. Fearfully hard to resist, this beer is loaded with brash citrus, grapefruit, orange, hints of resinous pine and touches of blackcurrant. Devilishly moreish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/89.png',7.5,70,1013,1068,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2011-01-01'),(90,'#Mashtag 2015','US Hopped Black Barley Wine.','05/2015','Democratically voted on by you and the BrewDog beer community. A wonderfully burnt toast malt backbone, loaded with American Hops for floral, citrus Flavours and warm boozy vanilla and toasted oak.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/90.png',10,85,1020,1098,130,65,4.4,79.6,20,25,21,'Oak Chips: 38.5g at FV, Vanilla Pods at FV','Oak Chips: 38.5g at FV, Vanilla Pods at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-05-01'),(91,'Dead Pony Club','West Coast Kicks. Citrusy. Zesty. Bright.','03/2012','Our California style West Coast IPA has light toffee and caramel notes layered on biscuit malt, supporting a huge, fresh citrus aroma, with lemongrass, lime zest, grapefruit peel, alongside some tropical notes, courtesy of some heavy-hitting US hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/91.png',3.8,35,1012,1040,25,12.7,4.4,70,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-03-01'),(92,'AB:09','Cranachan Imperial Stout.','11/2010','This Cranachan Imperial Stout was inspired by the famous Scottish dessert, and brewed with a mountain of dark malts, loads of oats, Scottish heather honey and local raspberries. The beer was then transferred to oak casks to mature for 6 months.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/92.png',11.6,77,1022,1110,265,132.5,5.2,80,20,25,19,'Lactose: 125g, Scottish Heather Honey: 125g, Raspberries: 187.5g','Lactose: 125g, Scottish Heather Honey: 125g, Raspberries: 187.5g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',15,'2010-11-01'),(93,'Mango Gose - B-Sides','Hoppy Mango Gose.','07/2015','Kettle soured hoppy mango gose. A delicate balance of sweet, juicy mango, sour lime and salinity.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.4,40,1000,1057,10,5,3.5,87,20,25,20,'Kettle Soured, 5 Mangoes pureed at FV','Kettle Soured, 5 Mangoes pureed at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-07-01'),(94,'Everday Anarchy','White Wine Barrel-Aged Imperial Red Saison.','06/2013','This French white wine barrel aged Imperial Saison has a plethora of intertwining Flavours. Huge aromas of peach, syrup, tangerine, sherry, toffee and raisin, followed by a dynamic bracing acidity.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/94.png',10.5,45,1005,1081,15,7.5,4.4,93.8,20,25,23,'Coriander seeds: 12.5g at End (WP), Orange: 25g at End (WP), Lemon: 25g at End (WP), Honey: 125g at End (WP), Pink Peppercorns: 3.5g at End (WP)','Coriander seeds: 12.5g at End (WP), Orange: 25g at End (WP), Lemon: 25g at End (WP), Honey: 125g at End (WP), Pink Peppercorns: 3.5g at End (WP)','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2013-06-01'),(95,'Peroxide Punk','Zesty Pale Ale.','04/2007','A trashy blonde concession for those who felt that our original 6% Punk IPA recipe was too hard hitting. This was also the first time we experimented with dry hopping our beers, giving Peroxide Punk a depth of Flavour that belies its modest ABV. Zesty, aromatic and thirst quenching.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4,40,1009,1039,18,9,4.4,76.9,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-04-01'),(96,'Lumberjack Stout','Blueberry Bacon Stout.','12/2013','Lumberjack Stout is an intense beast that took its inspriation from what an actual bona-fide lumberjack might have for breakfast. Flavours of molasses, chocolate, smoke, berry, coffee and more, with a low bitterness, leaning this beer firmly towards the malty side.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',15.2,20,1020,1110,158,79,4.4,82,20,25,21,'Blueberries, maple syrup and coffee, then aged in ex Grain whisky casks. Maple Syrup: 50g at end. Blueberries: 100g at middle.','Blueberries, maple syrup and coffee, then aged in ex Grain whisky casks. Maple Syrup: 50g at end. Blueberries: 100g at middle.','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',6,'2013-12-01'),(97,'Bowman\'s Beard - B-Sides','English Barley Wine.','03/2015','Ice-distilled double barley wine brewed by Chris from Stone Brewing Co. (see Sunmaid Stout) and BrewDog\'s own brewers. As robust, resinous and badass as its eponymic beard.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',18.3,50,1011,1067,15,8,5.3,84,20,25,19,'Ice-distilled after fermentation to get to 18.3%','Ice-distilled after fermentation to get to 18.3%','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',16,'2015-03-01'),(98,'Pumpkin King','Spicy Citrus Pumpkin Ale.','08/2015','We\'re turning Hallowe’en inside out and upside down. Pumpkin King is not your usual unctuous, cloyingly sweet Hallowe’en pumpkin ale. Sure, there’s a huge heady hit of pungent spice on the nose, but it’s followed with bright and zesty citrus Flavours, and a light mouthfeel. Spicy and sweet autumnal favourites like toasted marshmallow and toffee apple are just some of the complex notes you’ll find in our twisted take on a pumpkin ale, which weighs in at 5.4% ABV.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/98.png',5.4,20,1014,1055,30,15,4.4,74.6,20,25,19,'Pumkin puree: 375g, Grains of Paradise: 2.5g at end, Star Anise: 1.5g at end, Cinnamon: 2.5g at end, Nutmeg: 2.5g at end, Allspice: 2.5g at end, Ginger: 2.5g at end, Clove: 2.5g at end','Pumkin puree: 375g, Grains of Paradise: 2.5g at end, Star Anise: 1.5g at end, Cinnamon: 2.5g at end, Nutmeg: 2.5g at end, Allspice: 2.5g at end, Ginger: 2.5g at end, Clove: 2.5g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-08-01'),(99,'Hello My Name Is Päivi','Sea Buckthorn Double IPA.','05/2014','Brewed with sea buckthorn, a tart and bitter berry found on the Finnish coastline. Bright, vibrant aromas of tangerine, mandarin and peach, with zesty hits of lime, envelop the nutty, caramel malt backbone. The intense fruitiness gives a jammy quality to the nose. On the palate is a warm biscuity sweetness, with tropical fruits in a supporting role to a huge grapefruit and orange bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/99.png',8.3,70,1013,1076,30,15,4.4,82.9,20,25,21,'Sea Buckthorn Puree: 375g at end, EXP 366: 37.5g at dry hop','Sea Buckthorn Puree: 375g at end, EXP 366: 37.5g at dry hop','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-05-01'),(100,'Elvis Juice V2.0 - Prototype Challenge','Citrus Infused IPA.','12/2015','Punchy resinous hoppy aromas blast from the glass; light floral and citrus notes riff against huge piney character. Showcasing Citra, Simcoe and Amarillo at their absolute best. A huge dose of grapefruit peel brings swirls of fresh pithy zest, accentuating the dry hops and building on the dry, biscuit malt base.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/100.png',6.5,60,1010,1060,25,12.5,4.4,83.3,20,25,19,'Add grapefruit and orange peel into the boil and FV for extra citrus twist','Add grapefruit and orange peel into the boil and FV for extra citrus twist','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-12-01'),(101,'Riptide','Twisted Merciless Stout.','04/2007','The original BrewDog, Bracken decided to make a beer that best reflected himself; this is the beer equivalent of the big, cute chocolate monster. Soft, smooth, dark, chocolatey and a force to be reckoned with. This gentle giant will never bite, but you\'ll still want to be on your best behaviour!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/101.png',8,45,1014,1075,240,120,4.4,81.3,20,25,20,'Dark muscavado sugar 285g 30mins pre boil end','Dark muscavado sugar 285g 30mins pre boil end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2007-04-01'),(102,'Peach Therapy','Tart Belgian Tripple.','06/2015','9% abv sour tripel, infused with peach and apricot in collaboration with some of our favourite beer writers Adrian Tierney-Jones, Matt Curtis and Jonny and Brad from The Craft Beer Channel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',9,30,1000,1071,12,6,3.6,87,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2015-06-01'),(103,'Clown King','US Style Barley Wine.','12/2013','A heavy hitting combination of rich malt Flavours and relentless, bitter hops. Aromas of caramel and toasted marshmallow, with raisin and dried fruit, alongside a spicy undercurrent of resin. With toasty malt and sweet dark fruit Flavours, and a smooth, chewy mouthfeel, you’ll be lulled into a false sense of security, before the intense pine-sap resin draws out a huge bitter finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/103.png',12,85,1020,1130,24,12,4.4,102.3,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',6,'2013-12-01'),(104,'India Pale Weizen (w/ Weihenstephan)','BrewDog Versus Weihenstephan.','09/2014',' BrewDog vs. Weihenstephan India Pale Weizen kicked off a new direction for our collaborations. We took a simple concept (by our standards) and teamed up with the oldest brewery in the world to brew a mash-up beer using the signature styles of both breweries. India Pale Weizen has classic base hefeweizen aromas and Flavours of banana, clove and bubblegum, with a distinctive haziness. Layered on top of this is a tapestry of US citrus hop character. India Pale Weizen is a perfect symbiosis of traditional and modern brewing.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/104.png',6.2,50,1010,1056,35,17.5,4,85,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',8,'2014-09-01'),(105,'Hello My Name Is Beastie','Double IPA Brewed with Brambles.','08/2012','A Scottish take on Hello My Name is Ingrid with added brambles. Caramel malt provides sweetness to balance the tart berry character, which loses sweetness during fermentation.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/105.png',8.2,42,1013,1078,90,45,4.4,83.3,20,25,21,'500g bramble addition in the FV','500g bramble addition in the FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-08-01'),(106,'Punk IPA 2010 - Current','Post Modern Classic. Spiky. Tropical. Hoppy.','10/2010','Punk IPA. Amplified. In 2010 we finally got our paws on the equipment we needed to dry hop our beers. We focused all our energy on dry hopping, amping up the aroma and Flavour of our flagship beer to create a relentless explosion of tropical fruits, and adding a hint of Caramalt to balance out the insane amount of hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/106.png',5.6,40,1011,1055,15,7.6,4.4,78,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2010-10-01'),(107,'HBC 366 - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2014','A new, at-the-time un-named American hop now known as Equinox. Piney, resinous with spicy fruit notes and biting grapefruit. Stewed orange and pineapple with a resinous edge.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/107.png',7.2,70,1012,1067,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-02-01'),(108,'American Ale','Unleash the Yeast Series.','09/2013','Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and Flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit Flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. American Ale used a clean fermenting strain which provides some faint fruity notes.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/108.png',6.3,55,1012,1060,30,15,4.4,80,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',6,'2013-09-01'),(109,'Cocoa Psycho','Russian Imperial Stout. Rich. Decadent. Mocha.','11/2012','Vanilla pods and toasted oak chips add a rounded character to this massive Russian Imperial Stout, brewed with a hefty malt bill, cacao nibs and coffee beans. Dark malts combine with Cascade to add a punchy bitterness, strong enough to offset the big chocolate sweetness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/109.png',10,85,1012,1098,30,15.25,4.4,70,20,25,21,'Coffee Beans: 25g at end, Cocoa Nibs: 25g at end, Cocoa Nibs: 25g at conditioning, Coffee Beans: 25g at conditioning, Oak Chips: 15g at conditioning','Coffee Beans: 25g at end, Cocoa Nibs: 25g at end, Cocoa Nibs: 25g at conditioning, Coffee Beans: 25g at conditioning, Oak Chips: 15g at conditioning','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-11-01'),(110,'Truffle and Chocolate Stout - B-Sides','Gastronomic Session Stout.','03/2015','Pilot Brew - Truffle & Chocolate Stout. Deep, earthy roast notes make this a gastronome\'s dream.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.6,30,1015,1058,54,27,4.4,74,20,25,19,'Use Perigold Truffles after fermentation','Use Perigold Truffles after fermentation','Iain Mullan <iainmullan>',1,'2015-03-01'),(111,'Vagabond Pilsner','Hoppy Pilsner.','02/2013','Take the thirst-quenching crispness of a German Pilsner and combine it with lemon and honey to produce a rewarding modern twist on a beer classic.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/111.png',4.5,55,1012,1046,25,12.5,4.4,73.9,20,25,9,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2013-02-01'),(112,'Vote Sepp','Witbier With Hibiscus.','05/2014','Vote Sepp is a single hop wheat beer brewed to a session strength, with hibiscus flower, which gives it an impressively vibrant shade of pink. What Vote Sepp lacks in complexity, it more than makes up for in a perfect balance of tartness, bitterness and body.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/112.png',3.6,20,1009,1036,8,4,4.1,75,20,25,21,'Hibiscus: 37.5g Tank','Hibiscus: 37.5g Tank','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',17,'2014-05-01'),(113,'Hello My Name Is Ingrid','Sophisticated Bergmanesque Beer.','12/2010','A Double IPA with cloudberries added to the conditioning tank. One thing is certain – this Swedish inspired Double IPA is not as innocent as she first appears. A seductive body of rich malts and a buxom amount of Citra, Nelson Sauvin and Bramling Cross hops have been added to fresh Scandinavian cloudberries to deliver this beer’s tart finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/113.png',8.2,42,1013,1078,70,35,4.4,83.3,20,25,22,'Cloudberries: 1kg','Cloudberries: 1kg','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-12-01'),(114,'U-Boat (w/ Victory Brewing)','Smoked Porter Collab With Victory Brewing.','07/2014','On the palate is a big dark malt sweetness, balanced by the blend of spicy Mittelfruh and citrussy Galena. Cocoa powder, rich dark chocolate, and ripe berries interplay with a toasty burnt sugar bitterness. The mouthfeel is thick and chewy with a treacly quality that doesn’t cloy, as it plays off against the hops and roast malt bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/114.png',8.4,50,1015,1080,200,100,4.4,81.3,20,25,14,'Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2014-07-01'),(115,'Melon And Cucumber IPA - B-Sides','Fresh Melon IPA.','03/2015','A Pilot Brew with 200Kg of fresh melon and 5Kg fresh cucumber added after fermentation to produce the perfect summer refreshment.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6,50,1010,1050,8,4,5.2,87,20,25,20,'Melon: 500g, Cucumber: 20g','Melon: 500g, Cucumber: 20g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(116,'Morag\'s Mojito - B-Sides','Cocktail Meets Beer.','08/2015','A cunning cocktail blend of grapefruit hops, ginger spice and refreshing mint.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.7,40,1010,1063,15,7.5,5.2,84,20,25,19,'Fresh mint leaves after fermentation, Grains of Paradise: 6.5g at end, Fresh Limes: 50g at end.','Fresh mint leaves after fermentation, Grains of Paradise: 6.5g at end, Fresh Limes: 50g at end.','Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2015-08-01'),(117,'Hop Rocker','Hoppy Aggressive Lager','04/2007','The first of our foray into lager beer, Hop Rocker is a high impact, hoppy behemoth made with 100% malt. Since 2007 we have been obsessive about quality, using only the best ingredients to ensure the Flavour and craftsmanship of the beer in your glass. Hop Rocker is testament to that. The malt base gives this beer a sweet, balanced complexity while the combination of New Zealand and German hops merges new world tropical juiciness with old world peppery spice.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/117.png',5.5,40,1010,1052,25,12,4.2,80.7,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',5,'2007-04-01'),(118,'Bounty Hunter - Shareholder Brew','Beatnik Milk Stout.','02/2015','Brewed with our Equity Punks this rich, smooth stout is brewed with a blend of six malts, resulting in a welcoming, resonant black beer. From start to finish it carries an intense roastiness reminiscent of dark chocolate intertwined with a delicate hint of coconut and caramel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/118.png',6.5,35,1020,1068,250,125,4.2,70.6,20,25,19,'Cacao Nibs: 25g at end, Coconut Chips: 20g at end, Lactose (wk): 375g at end, Coconut Chips: 50g at FV','Cacao Nibs: 25g at end, Coconut Chips: 20g at end, Lactose (wk): 375g at end, Coconut Chips: 50g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-02-01'),(119,'Zeitgeist','Organic Black Lager.','12/2008','Zeitgeist is an idiosyncratic alternative black lager. Its inspiration is found more than 200 years ago. Zeitgeist takes an age old classic, a forgotten masterpiece, and gives it relevance and an avant-garde edge.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/119.png',4.9,32,1010,1047.5,120,60,4.3,79,20,25,15,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',5,'2008-12-01'),(120,'AB:10','Imperial Brown Ale Aged In Spanish Red Wine Barrels.','10/2011','A decadent, robust and encapsulating Imperial Ale. A rollercoaster of devilish berries, smooth vanilla, toasted marshmallow and wine gums; caramel malt balanced with moderate bitterness and a roasty edge.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/120.png',11.5,80,1020,1096,115,57.5,4.4,79.2,20,25,20,'Age in red wine barrels','Age in red wine barrels','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-10-01'),(121,'Punk Monk','Who Ordered The Belgian Yeast?','07/2009','Old world meets new in this trans-atlantic mash up of brewing ingredients. Belgian funk incorporates itself into the pithy, resin and grapefruit, with pineapple and banana rounding out a rambunctious avalanche of fruity hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6,60,1010,1056,17,8.5,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2009-07-01'),(122,'Dog Fight (w/ Flying Dog)','Rye IPA - Flying Dog Collab.','10/2012','A clash of kings. A spiced toffee malt backbone arranged against a tidal wave of US hops. Citrus, nectarine and juicy tropical fruits are layered into this complex beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',8.5,65,1012,1078,31.2,15.6,4.4,84.6,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-10-01'),(123,'Candy Kaiser','NorDdeutsches Retro Altbier.','08/2015','In this northern German style retro altbier, we’ve dialled down the dry-hops to zero, but cranked up the malt to create massive aromas. Toasty, toffee and floral notes duke it out for supremacy in the headspace of your glass. When this all hits your palate, the steely bitterness combines with the rich dry malt and the subtle alcohol warmth in a full throttle attack on your taste buds.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/123.png',5.2,45,1009,1049,45,22.5,4.2,81.6,20,25,14,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-08-01'),(124,'Chaos Theory','Predictably Random IPA.','10/2008','Chaos Theory is the most under- rated achievement of 20th Century science. This beer can only aspire to parallel to the mathematical use of the word chaos, which is at odds to the common parlance. The purest showcase of the magnificent hop that is Nelson Sauvin; grapefruit, pineapple and caramel sing above the chaos of life.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/124.png',7.1,90,1013,1067,15,7.5,4.4,80.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-10-01'),(125,'Juniper Wheat Beer','American Style Wheat Ale With Juniper Berries.','06/2011','A variant on the 2008 release of Bad Pixie, but hoppier. Substituting the lemon peel for Ahtanum provided a vibrant floral and lemon citrus hit, balancing the slight tartness from the wheat. This dry, effervescent brew is perfect on Scotland\'s one day of summer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5,40,1008,1047,15,7.5,4.1,83,20,25,17,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',10,'2011-06-01'),(126,'Jet Black Heart','Oatmeal Milk Stout. Dark. Roasty. Velvety.','01/2016','Good things come to those who wait. This smooth and roasty oatmeal milk stout won our 2015 Prototype Challenge at a canter. Roasty coffee and chocolate lead to a decadent, full-bodied richness of near uncharted depths with a velvet mouthfeel from the addition of oatmeal and a touch of wheat. This is complemented at every turn by the Magnum and Sorachi Ace hops, with the latter bringing an intensity of smooth vanilla and dark berry fruit on the long, rewarding finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/126.png',4.7,45,1019,1055,200,100,4.4,70,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sasha <SashaMasondeCaires>',1,'2016-01-01'),(127,'Galaxy','Single Hop India Pale Ale – 2012.','02/2012','With all the rich tropical Flavour you\'d expect from Australia\'s Galaxy, this beer backs up a strong citrus aroma and Flavour with a mellow undercurrent of passion fruit and mango. Zingy and sweet but not too sweet, Galaxy has a soft and inviting fruity hop character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/127.png',6.7,67,1064,1013,19,9.5,4.4,79.7,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-02-01'),(128,'White Noise','White IPA with Motueka.','07/2012','A White IPA; brewed with plenty of wheat, fermented with a Belgian yeast with some coriander thrown in for good measure. Oh and this one has mountains of Motueka hops. And then lots of dry hops too.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.8,50,1012,1060,30,15,4.4,80,20,25,18,'Coriander powder: 37.5g at end','Coriander powder: 37.5g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',17,'2012-07-01'),(129,'Hinterland','A Most Beguiling Brew.','05/2015','Hinterland is a beer long in the creation, and even longer in the appreciation. On the aroma, deep reverberating roasty bitterness and sweet dark chocolate. Also in evidence, woodsmoke, rich vanilla, mocha and marzipan. When tasting, Hinterland reveals itself as the beer moves from cellar temperature to something warmer, yielding all of the above plus dried fruit, rich ganache and ending on a resoundingly warming finish redolent of chocolate liqueur or plum brandy.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/129.png',9,85,1025,1094,400,200,4.3,73.4,20,25,21,'Lactose (Milk Sugar): 500g at middle','Lactose (Milk Sugar): 500g at middle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-05-01'),(130,'Spiced Cherry Sour - B-Sides','Alternative Festive.','03/2015','Think bakewell tart with Christmas spices.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.5,20,1010,1060,NULL,NULL,3.2,87,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(131,'Motueka','Single Hop India Pale Ale – 2012.','02/2012','Lemon and lime rise to the top of this hoppy brew, with supporting acts of tropical fruit for a very rounded, thoroughly satisfying Flavour. Motueka is a hop we\'ve used in loads of recipes; it has enough resin to balance the intense fruity character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/131.png',6.7,67,1064,1013,19,9.5,4.4,79.7,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-02-01'),(132,'5am Saint','Bittersweet Chaos. Malty. Fruity. Bite.','06/2009','Out of order and stability comes the rush of the pack. Berry and caramel riding alongside marmalade and chocolate. Spice and toast jostle with lychee and biscuit. The needle flicks to all points of the compass. It drives you towards the horizon, towards the vanishing point. And it keeps going...','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/132.png',5,30,1012,1050,60,30.5,4.4,76,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2009-06-01'),(133,'Black Eye Joe (w/ Stone Brewing Co)','Coffe Black IPA.','11/2013','A fresh tropical hit from this Black IPA, with undertones of roasted coffee. A well balanced, drinkable yet complex beer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.8,40,1008,1053,177.3,88.7,4.4,84.9,20,25,19,'Fresh coffee in the boil.','Fresh coffee in the boil.','Ali Skinner <Ali SKinner>',1,'2013-11-01'),(134,'Mr.Miyagi\'s Wasabi Stout','Spicy Stout Brewed By Aberdeen Bar Staff.','09/2011','Invented by and brewed by Dan Bloxham, no matter what anyone else says. A medium bodied, bitter, US style stout, with a wasabi warmth, a subtle earthiness and a hint of soy sauce.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.5,90,1015,1072,200,102,4.4,79.2,20,25,21,'Wasabi Powder: 45g at end, Wasabi Paste: 75g at end','Wasabi Powder: 45g at end, Wasabi Paste: 75g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-09-01'),(135,'Growler','Citra Hopped Pilsner','03/2011','Brewed by Pivovar Group at BrewDog, specifically for thier bars, Pivo in Leeds, Sheffield Tap in Sheffield, and Euston Tap in Euston. It was then lagered for 2 months and dry hopped with citra.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.5,38,1008,1042.9,18,9,4.4,81,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2011-03-01'),(136,'#Mashtag 2014','Democratic Imperial Red Ale.','05/2014','A slightly psychotic, orange-that- thinks-it’s-a-grapefruit character builds upon and intensifies the hop bitterness, squaring up against the rich sweet malt base. The result is a huge Red Ale with a drinkable quality you’d expect in a beer half this strength.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/136.png',9,50,1015,1084,20,10,4.4,82.1,20,25,21,'Blood Orange: 250g at end, Lemon Peel: 3.9g at end, Orange Peel: 7.7g at end','Blood Orange: 250g at end, Lemon Peel: 3.9g at end, Orange Peel: 7.7g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-05-01'),(137,'Sink The Bismarck!','IPA For The Dedicated.','12/2009','This is IPA amplified, the most evocative style of the craft beer resistance with the volume cranked off the scale. Kettle hopped, dry hopped then freeze hopped for a deep fruit, resinous and spicy aroma. A full on attack on your taste buds ensues as the incredibly smooth liquid delivers a crescendo of malt, sweet honey, hop oils and a torpedo of hop bitterness that lasts and lasts.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/137.png',41,1085,1016,1085,40,20,4.4,81.2,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2009-12-01'),(138,'Dog A','Cacao, Coffee, Chili Imperial Anniversary Stout.','05/2012','Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn\'t change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chili warmth of this monumental stout.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/138.png',15,90,1003,1120,100,50,4.4,98,20,25,19,'Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chili.','Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chili.','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-05-01'),(139,'Born To Die','Terminally Hoppy India Pale Ale.','03/2015','Savagely bitter, exceptionally dry, this IPA is born to die on a predetermined day. It proudly displays its short-lived life span front and centre. There is no better time to drink this than the moment you get your paws on it. Awesome bitterness backed up by unrelenting aromas of resin, citrus, and juicy fruit. Born To Die is a eulogy to the hops that sacrificed themselves in its creation. An incredibly ambitious and satisfying small batch brew.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/139.png',8.5,85,1007,1072,15,7.5,4.4,90.3,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-03-01'),(140,'Pioneer - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','03/2015','2015 IPA is Dead Series. Pioneer hails from the hop gardens of Kent, and for those expecting something classically English, they surprise with an unforeseen blast of lemony citrus. Bookended with a herbal, cedar quality, these high alpha UK hops pack a pithy zing not often seen from these hop-growing isles.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/140.png',7.2,100,1010,1064,12,6,4.4,84,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(141,'Cap Dog (w/ Cap Brewery)','Black Cascara IPA.','08/2014','A collaboration by BrewDog and CAP with Cascara green unroasted cherry coffee beans.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/141.png',9,80,1014,1083,180,90,5.2,83.1,20,25,21,'Cascara: 500g','Cascara: 500g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-08-01'),(142,'Orange Blossom - B-Sides','Citrus Wheat Braggot.','08/2015','Orange blossom honey braggot. A floral easy drinker with a hint of citrus.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.8,20,1000,1039,6,3,5.2,87,20,25,20,'Orange blossom honey: 1kg in FV.','Orange blossom honey: 1kg in FV.','Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2015-08-01'),(143,'Lizard Bride - Prototype Challenge','Fruit Infused Sour IPA.','07/2015','Wonderfully tart, bitter, piney and filled with the fruity elements from raspberries, blueberries and sour cherries. Oh, and it’s purple.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/143.png',5.7,35,1009,1053,25,12.5,4.4,79.3,20,25,17,'Blackcurrant: 65g at FV, Sour Cherry: 65g at FV, Blueberry: 65g at FV, Sea Buckthorn: 65g at FV, Cranberry: 65g at FV, Blackberry: 65g at FV, Sweet cherry: 65g at FV','Blackcurrant: 65g at FV, Sour Cherry: 65g at FV, Blueberry: 65g at FV, Sea Buckthorn: 65g at FV, Cranberry: 65g at FV, Blackberry: 65g at FV, Sweet cherry: 65g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-07-01'),(144,'Tokyo*','Intergalactic Stout. Rich. Smoky. Fruity.','06/2009','Our most involved beer, Tokyo* is an Imperial Stout brewed with copious amounts of specialty malts, jasmine and cranberries, dry-hopped with a bucket-load of our favourite hops and then carefully aged on toasted French oak chips. It’s all about moderation. Everything in moderation, including moderation itself...','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/144.png',16.2,85,1028,1157,250,127,4.4,82.2,20,25,21,'Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at middle, Oak chips: 15g at FV','Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at middle, Oak chips: 15g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',11,'2009-06-01'),(145,'Sorachi Bitter - B-Sides','Sorachi Ace Bitter.','03/2015','Pilot Brew: A twist on an English Bitter style beer, using Sorachi Ace hops throughout making a showcase of the off the dill and lemon character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.3,130,1010,1060,14,7,5.2,83,20,25,20,'This beer was unfiltered to give it a traditional ale appearance, Indian Coriander: 2.5g at end','This beer was unfiltered to give it a traditional ale appearance, Indian Coriander: 2.5g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(146,'Nelson Sauvin','Single Hop IPA Series – 2011.','01/2011','Nelson is a love it or hate it kinda hop. We are cool with that, if we wanted to keep everyone happy we would be brewing Fosters anyway. Sharp as a razor, this New Zealand hop slices its way through your taste buds and is brutally resinous, almost scraping the intense Flavours of passion fruit along your poor tongue. There is a huge depth of tropical fruit Flavour with astringent gooseberry balanced against the robust malt base. Throw another shrimp on the barbie mate and you are all set. New Zealand is near Austria, right?','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/146.png',7.5,75,1013,1068,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2011-01-01'),(147,'Hello My Name Is Little Ingrid','Cloudberry Session IPA.','03/2015','This beer hits all the high-points of Hello My Name is Ingrid – with one important exception. Brewed at 4.4% abv, Little Ingrid is a session- strength version of our cloudberry- infused celebration of all that is epic about Sweden. The zesty balance of citrus from the four different hops is just as pronounced as in the original.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/147.png',4.4,35,1012,1045,30,15,4.4,73.3,20,25,19,'Cloudberries: 27.5g at end','Cloudberries: 27.5g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(148,'AB:02','Triple Dry Hopped Imperial Red Ale.','05/2010','The second installation in the Abstrakt Concept beer line up. All the benefits of a malty biscuited red ale, layered with tons of hops. We recommend ageing this beer for 6 months. Try one now, and one for later.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/148.png',18,70,1010,1150,57,28.5,4.4,93.3,20,25,22,'Add white sugar to the fermentation to keep the yeast fermenting and produce more alcohol','Add white sugar to the fermentation to keep the yeast fermenting and produce more alcohol','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-05-01'),(149,'AB:03','Barrel-Aged Imperial Ale.','09/2008','This Abstrakt started life as a simple imperial Ale, but upon the addition of fresh Scottish raspberries and strawberries, and left to mature for 2 years in Invergordon whisky casks that had held whisky for over 40 years, this beer transcended into something new.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/149.png',10.5,14,1013,1093,NULL,NULL,4.4,80,20,25,19,'Strawberries: 1kg, Raspberries: 1kg, Oak Chips: 75g','Strawberries: 1kg, Raspberries: 1kg, Oak Chips: 75g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2008-09-01'),(150,'AB:13','Cask-Aged Cherry Imperial Stout.','01/2012','A cherry imperial stout aged in ex- sherry whisky barrels. Based on the classic German Schwarzwald (Black Forest) dessert. Intense dark fruit Flavours of cherry, plum, raisin and currant, coupled with deep bitter chocolate, espresso and a full- bodied coffee and cream character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/150.png',11.3,50,1020,1098,164,83,4.4,79.6,20,25,20,'Lactose: 125g at middle, Sour cherries: 187.5g at middle','Lactose: 125g at middle, Sour cherries: 187.5g at middle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-01-01'),(151,'Rhubarb Saison - B-Sides','Spiced Rhubarb Saison.','10/2015','Spiced peppercorn and rhubarb Saison.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.4,25,1008,1052,10,5,5.2,87,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2015-10-01'),(152,'Deaf Mermaid - B-Sides','Light Pale Ale.','04/2015','A keg-only summer special, hop- bursted and dry-hopped to infinity.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.2,65,1010,1048,16,8,5.2,79,20,25,19,'Most of the hops are added in the whirlpool and dry hop stages','Most of the hops are added in the whirlpool and dry hop stages','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-04-01'),(153,'Hoppy Saison - B-Sides','Hop Yeast Synergy.','03/2015','Hoppy citrus and tropical fruit Saison.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.4,40,1010,1059,8,4,5.2,87,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',18,'2015-03-01'),(154,'No Label','Dry Hopped Kölsch.','10/2015','No Label is a postmodern, postgender non-binary brew; the world’s first beer made with transgender hops. Brewed with whole hop bines that have spontaneously changed from female to male, no label goes its own way. No Label balances a light, biscuity dryness from the malt base with delicate hints of fruity esters gifted by the fermentation. Finally, dry- hopping adds a layer of new world tropical & pine Flavours that add a unique twist to this classic Kölsch style beer. All profits from the sales of this beer were donated to LGBTQI+ events organisers Queerest of the Queer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/154.png',4.5,25,1009,1043,10,5,4.2,79.1,20,25,15,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-10-01'),(156,'Old World Russian Imperial Stout','Russian Imperial Stout.','10/2011','This Old World Stout perfectly recreates the export stouts of years gone by; brewed to imperial strength to avoid freezing during its journey across the Baltic Sea to snowy Moscow. Full bodied with huge chocolate, coffee and roast Flavours, this imperial stout employs a variety of hops to add enough bitterness and hop complexity to balance the huge malt sweetness and rich mocha and molasses Flavours.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/155.png',9.5,80,1014,1075,195,97.5,4.5,81.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-10-01'),(157,'Hoppy Christmas','Simcoe Single-Hop India Pale Ale.','10/2012','Pineapple, citrus and papaya; single-hopped with Simcoe, Hoppy Christmas is an anti-festive IPA, redolent with summery Flavours. Small caramel malt additions provide a touch of malt complexity. Simcoe, arguably our favourite hop, carries this beer - pine, tropical fruit and bitterness are its specialities.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/156.png',7.2,70,1012,1067,30,15,4.4,82.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-10-01'),(158,'Edge','Dark Full-Bodied Cask Ale','12/2007','Low ABV, high Flavour, this beer was brewed to show that a beer can have all the Flavour without the drunken affects. Also this beer is one of BrewDog\'s original brews that made a rare appearance in cask. Spicy, malty biscuit and super drinkable.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/cask.png',2.7,36,1010,1033,57,29,4.4,70.8,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-12-01'),(159,'Hello My Name Is Zé (w/ 2Cabeças)','Passionfruit IPA - 2Cabecas Collab.','03/2014','Punk multiplied by Jack Hammer, divided by passionfruit with some Brazilian spirit factored in too. A well-rounded IPA, with bags of tropical Flavour boosted by the addition of passionfruit, which unsurprisingly dominates the aroma of this summery IPA.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/158.png',6.4,50,1012,1061,20,10,4.4,80.3,20,25,19,'Passionfruit: 438g at End','Passionfruit: 438g at End','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-03-01'),(160,'Black Tokyo Horizon (w/Nøgne Ø & Mikkeller)','Imperial Stout Collaboration.','12/2010','Special Collaboration between Nøgne, Mikkeller and BrewDog which is a recipe based on all three brewers’ big stouts; Nøgne Ø Dark Horizon, Mikkeller Black and BrewDog Tokyo*.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/159.png',17.2,75,1030,1156,128,64,4.4,80.8,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-12-01'),(161,'Restorative Beverage For Invalids And Convalescents','An Extract Taken From \"A Treatise on Food and Diet\" By Dr Jonathan Pereira, 1843.','02/2015','Brewed to 8.5%, light as a mass market Pilsner in colour, fermented to be as dry as a Lambic, but as bitter as any double IPA and loaded with as much hop aroma as we can get into a beer. The fermentables in this beer were Maris Otter Extra Pale along with plenty of sugar as we mashed at a very low temperature to ensure maximum fermentability and attenuation. This beer is fermented within an inch of its life making it dry, sheer and bright. Citra, Amarillo & Centennial were all used in abundance in the kettle and also fired extremely liberally at this beer with our high tech hop cannon.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/160.png',8.5,100,1003,1068,15,7.5,4.4,95.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2015-02-01'),(162,'Tokyo Rising Sun - Highland','A Beautiful Accident.','06/2009','A forgotten gem in the deepest, darkest corner of the warehouse. Aged in a Highland whisky cask resulting in a viscous slow motion roller coaster of powdered cacao, hints of burning pirate ships, salted caramel, sharp berries and toasted marshmallow.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/161.png',13.2,85,1023,1125,140,71,4.4,82.17,20,25,21,'Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 500g at start, Oak chips soaked in lowland whisky: 15g at dry hop','Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 500g at start, Oak chips soaked in lowland whisky: 15g at dry hop','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',11,'2009-06-01'),(163,'77 Lager','Artisan Rebel Pilsner.','12/2008','Think of everything you know about lagers. Then forget it all instantly. 77 will redefine the experience forever. A Lager that actually tastes of something? You have to be kidding, right? 77 lager is made with 100% malt and whole leaf hops. It contains no preservatives, additives, cheap substitutes or any other junk. Maybe we are crazy. So what? Taste 77 Lager and we are pretty sure you will agree that the fine line between genius and insanity has just become a little more blurred.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/162.png',4.9,30,1009,1047,12,6,4.4,80.7,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Mike Francis <mikeffrancis@gmail.com>',2,'2008-12-01'),(164,'This. Is. Lager','21st Century Pilsner. Sharp. Robust. Honest.','08/2014','Brewed with 100% malt, ten times the hops of most industrial lagers and cold-conditioned for five weeks, this spicy, robust Pilsner is lager reborn. Expect a robust, full-bodied malt character on the front of the tongue, spicy citrus notes as it goes back through the palate and an assertive bitter finish with a lemon and pepper character to round things off.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/163.png',4.7,37,1007,1043,10,6,4.2,83.7,20,25,12,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2014-08-01'),(165,'Ella - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','03/2015','2015 IPA is Dead Series. Supremely floral, this hugely under-rated hop is related to Galaxy and was first cultivated in the Australian state of Victoria. Initially given the same name as a certain Eurolager, their lawyers got involved and the St- prefix was dropped. Ella displays subtle notes of spice, but is fundamentally a truly floral bouquet, redolent of the Southern Hemisphere.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/164.png',7.2,100,1010,1064,12,6,4.4,84,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(166,'Barley Wine - Russian Doll','Double India Pale Ale.','06/2014','Russian Doll was an experimental set of brews showcasing the effects of varying the amount and ratio of malts in the grist. The barley wine had rich, chewy dark fruit aromas balanced with a spike of zesty hops. Toffee, apricot jam and grapefruit pith, crammed into the head of our little Russian Doll family.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/165.png',10,80,1020,1097,65,32.5,4.4,79.4,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-06-01'),(167,'Vagabond Pale ALe - Prototype Challenge','Gluten Free Beer. Toffee. Piney. Fruitcake.','11/2014','A foundation of caramel malt is buttressed by a raucously resinous bitterness, as the rioting backdrop of citrus and tropical fruit flow in waves from those twin titans of the US – Centennial and Amarillo. And it also happens to be gluten free.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/166.png',4.5,55,1011,1045,20,10,4.2,73.9,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-11-01'),(168,'Libertine Black Ale','The New Black. Roasty. Hoppy. Fruity.','03/2012','A dark hop bomb combining the malt-forward indulgences of a stout with the insatiable hopload of an IPA. Rich spiced blackcurrant and caramel up front, with a sharp bitter finish following behind, bringing grapefruit and resin with it. Dry, bitter and intense; this is an IPA first and foremost, given a dark malt makeover. Originally brewed as a Simcoe only single hop IPA, we\'ve experimented with adding a little Cascade and Mosaic for extra depth.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/167.png',7.2,50,1013,1068,150,76,4.4,78.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-03-01'),(169,'Jack Hammer','Ruthless India Pale Ale. Hoppy. Bitter. Hoppy.','06/2012','Hopped beyond the point at which IBUs are measurable, only the most hardened palate will get beyond Jack Hammer\'s intensely resinous pithy bitterness and to the grapefruit, orange zest and dry biscuity malt beyond. You could brew this with less hops, but really, why would you bother?','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/168.png',7.2,250,1010,1065,15,7.5,4.4,84.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-06-01'),(170,'AB:19','A Blend of Two Barrel-aged Imperial Saisons.','06/2012','One of the most complex beers we’ve ever attempted. A blend of two barrel-aged Imperial Saisons – one black, one red – which has in turn then been aged in rum barrels, it is an enormous, intricate beer. A baseline of warm, smoky raisin and plum, followed by punchy Flavour elements coming to the fore – coconut, mint and blackcurrant. There’s a long undercurrent of treacle toffee, before the finish darkens to liquorice, star anise amidst a touch of honey sweetness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/169.png',13.1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,20,25,NULL,'This beer is an odd one in our collection as it is a blend of two recipes that feature elsewhere. These recipes are #123 Everyday Anarchy and #124 Black Jacques. Both Imperial Saisons spent a little under a year in white and red wine barrels respectively. However, while the pair were being tasted to determine their readiness to be released, a fun game of blending turned into a light bulb moment. The beers were blended and laid down once more in our barrel cellar, this time being infused with the heady note of rum. We were so excited about this mystical blend that we ended up using up all the beer that had been lovingly aged. It would have been a travesty for these beers to go unrecognised as the unique individuals they were, so we brewed them again in 2013 to be released as had always been intended. Age the individual beers separately before blending and ageing further on oak chips soaked in rum.','This beer is an odd one in our collection as it is a blend of two recipes that feature elsewhere. These recipes are #123 Everyday Anarchy and #124 Black Jacques. Both Imperial Saisons spent a little under a year in white and red wine barrels respectively. However, while the pair were being tasted to determine their readiness to be released, a fun game of blending turned into a light bulb moment. The beers were blended and laid down once more in our barrel cellar, this time being infused with the heady note of rum. We were so excited about this mystical blend that we ended up using up all the beer that had been lovingly aged. It would have been a travesty for these beers to go unrecognised as the unique individuals they were, so we brewed them again in 2013 to be released as had always been intended. Age the individual beers separately before blending and ageing further on oak chips soaked in rum.','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',NULL,'2012-06-01'),(171,'Bashah (w/ Stone Brewing Co)','Black Belgian Double IPA.','08/2009','Brewed when our good friends from Stone visited in 2009. Black As Sin, Hoppy As Hell - no other beer name has quite hit the nail so squarely on the head. Dark roasted malt makes a beautiful canvas for the savage hop bitterness, pine needles and orange zest.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/170.png',9.7,100,1015,1088,30,15.3,4.4,83,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2009-08-01'),(172,'Challenger','Single Hop India Pale Ale – 2012.','02/2012','Challenger is known for its herbal and fruity characteristics. When used alone in a beer like IPA is Dead, Challenger brings light woodsy notes, floral hints, and delicate green tea, alongside more recognisable citrus notes. As a dual-purpose hop, it also yields great bittering potential, which is ideal in a dry bitter IPA.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/171.png',6.7,67,1013,1064,19,9.5,4.4,79.7,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-02-01'),(173,'Single Hop Enigma IPA - B-Sides','Enigma Hopped IPA.','01/2016','A cheeky play with a new hop on the pilot kit. Expect notes of redcurrant, melon and citrus. An intriguing possibility for the future.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5,50,1011,1050,10,5,4.4,78,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',16,'2016-01-01'),(174,'Chinook - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','03/2015','2015 IPA is Dead series. Often used as a combination hop for American Pale Ales and IPAs, Chinook can really shine when left to front a beer all on its own. The main reason for this is that it’s thunderously piney, with a fistful of spice kicked up in your face as you lie on the beach. A true heavyweight of the brewing industry.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/173.png',7.2,100,1010,1064,12,6,4.4,84,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-03-01'),(175,'Konnichiwa Kitsune','Hello My Name Is Yuzu.','10/2014','Named in a slight deviation from our Hello My Name Is series, Konnichiwa Kitsune is a Japanese- inspired, yuzu-infused Imperial IPA, brewed with Amarillo, Cascade and Citra. These punchy new world hops bring orange, grapefruit and lime to back up the yuzu aroma and Flavour. Big mandarin notes, balanced against a caramel malt biscuity base.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/174.png',4.4,70,1012,1045,30,15,4.4,82.9,20,25,20,'Yuzu juice: 250g at FV','Yuzu juice: 250g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2014-10-01'),(176,'San Diego Scotch Ale (w/Ballast Point)','Imperial Scotch Ale With Rum & Raisin.','07/2012','Whisky cask aged with raisins soaked in rum. Warm, chocolatey and boozy with refreshing resinous bitterness and a lingering toasty biscuit background from the malt. Toasted oak comes courtesy of the barrels and spicy, sweet, dark fruit Flavours from the rum soaked raisins.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/175.png',9,70,1018,1090,190,95,4.4,80,20,25,21,'Age in whisky casks with rum soaked raisins','Age in whisky casks with rum soaked raisins','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-07-01'),(177,'Old World India Pale Ale','English India Pale Ale.','10/2011','This recreated the epic IPAs that were sent on monumental ocean voyages from England to India by sea in the 1800s. Medium bodied with a complex malt profile, backed up with intense bitterness and a woodsy, earthy rich English hop character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/176.png',7.5,80,1012,1069,50,25,4.4,82.6,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2011-10-01'),(178,'Dog D','Anniversary Imperial Stout.','05/2015','Dog D is an extra special brew, marking 8 years of BrewDog. Like Dog A, B & C before it, Dog D is an Imperial Stout with speciality ingredients, only this time we’ve barrel-aged it too. Dog D pours like dark matter into your glass, with a deep tan head. The nose is subtle but powerful, and on the palate, there’s a treacle toffee backbone, supporting the spicy hop Flavour and naga chilli heat.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/177.png',16.1,85,1015,1125,400,200,4.3,84,20,25,21,'Add 1 naga chilli in the FV','Add 1 naga chilli in the FV','Joakim Skoog <joakimskoog>',6,'2015-05-01'),(179,'Simcoe','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','01/2012','A special release of our IPA is Dead series - IPA is Dead Simoce. Hopped to hell with citrusy bitter and aroma hops from the West Coast of the USA. Bitter, orange, mandarin, floral, this IPA showcases the best the west has to offer.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/178.png',6.7,70,1012,1063,30,15,4.4,81,20,25,99,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-01-01'),(180,'How To Disappear Completely','Fake Fix Double IPA.','04/2009','Jam-packed with two of our favourite hops - Columbus and Centennial, it has 198 (yes one hundred and ninety eight) theoretical IBUs. We use a lot of caramalt, some amber malt and some chocolate malt to give the little beer as much body and mouthfeel as possible and the ability to handle all the hops we threw at it. We think this beer is the world’s first ever Imperial Mild. Imperial in terms of hop profile. An Imperially Hopped Mild. BrewDog’s Imperial Mild. How to Disappear Completely.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/179.png',3.5,198,1010,1037,37,19,4.4,73,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2009-04-01'),(181,'Doodlebug','Hoppy Sub-Session Pale Ale.','09/2015','Doodlebug is our fusion of low strength and enormously high tropical hop levels – think a mashup of Hop Fiction and How to Disappear Completely, and you’re almost there. Clocking in at 2.8% ABV, Doodlebug is keg-only and is packed with Amarillo, Chinook and Mosaic; letting fly a hoppy buzzbomb at sub-session-strength.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',2.5,35,1008,1027,10,5,4.2,70.4,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Lars Gregori <choas>',1,'2015-09-01'),(182,'Vic Secret','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','10/2013','Piney, citrusy and resinous with herbal notes, Vic Secret is dual-purpose (Flavour & bitterness) perfect for brewing up a single hop IPA.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.4,70,1012,1069,30,15,4.4,82.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-10-01'),(183,'All Day Long - Prototype Challenge','Malty Low ABV Ale.','11/2014','Prototype Challenge 2014. All Day Long is a mild like no other. This complex, low-alcohol brew was the third of our 2014 Prototypes. Featuring a boatload of seven different speciality malts and some of our favourite hops, this beer is resinous at first, transitioning into something akin to bitter orange marmalade spread onto a thick bread crust. This is for everyone who said BrewDog would never brew a mild...','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/182.png',2.8,30,1012,1032.5,42,21,4.4,63.1,20,25,22,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-11-01'),(184,'Nuns With Guns','Dry-Hopped Lager.','11/2012','A dry-hopped Session Pilsner. At 4.2% this amber-hued lager packs a malty punch with toasty Munich character and a light caramel sweetness. From here, things take a sharp turn towards the hoppy Flavour, with some serious US citrus packed classic hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/183.png',4.2,25,1012,1044,19,9.5,4.4,72.7,20,25,16,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2012-11-01'),(185,'Atlantic IPA Ale','IPA Of Yesteryear.','12/2008','Like IPA historically would have been. Part of this beer was aged on a fishing boat in an oak cask and released as \"Atlantic IPA\".','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/184.png',8,80,1013,1074,55,13,4.4,82,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',13,'2008-12-01'),(186,'Tactical Nuclear Penguin','Uber Imperial Stout.','09/2009','This beer is about pushing the boundaries, it is about taking innovation in beer to a whole new level. Dark and decadent, plum, treacle and roast coffee are amplified beyond any stout you\'ve had before.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/185.png',32,1157,1028,1157,250,127,4.4,82.2,20,25,21,'Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at start, Oak chips: 15g at FV','Cranberry: 25g at end, Jasmine: 25g at end, Muscovado sugar: 300g at start, Oak chips: 15g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',11,'2009-09-01'),(187,'Jasmine IPA','Floral & Fruity India Pale Ale.','03/2014','This has big floral aromas backed up with some of our favourite fruity hop Flavours. Bitter, bright and refreshing, our Jasmine IPA is a perfect spring beer for drinking outside (under a patio heater, with a pair of gloves on).','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.8,40,1014,1060,35,17.5,4.4,76.7,20,25,19,'Jasmine addition in cold conditioning','Jasmine addition in cold conditioning','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-03-01'),(188,'Lichtenstein Pale Ale','Us-Hopped Rye Pale Ale.','01/2013','Dry-hopped with some of our hop heroes, bringing incredibly fruity aromas of zesty orange, pithy grapefruit, pungent pine and resin, backed up with spicy, toasty malt Flavours of toffee, biscuit, rye bread and toast crust.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/187.png',5.2,50,1010,1050,17,8.5,4.4,80,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2013-01-01'),(189,'Paradox Jura','Ubiquitous Imperial Stout.','06/2010','Paradox. Reloaded. In 2011 we put Paradox into high gear to create an Imperial Stout destined for ageing. Loaded with dark roasted malts for a full bodied, toasted background, an array of bitter, earthy and resinous hops, and brewed with oats for a bold mouthfeel. This beer is the perfect canvas for barrel ageing.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/188.png',10,55,1014,1128,300,152,4.4,89,20,25,21,'Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Try ageing on oak chips, infusing with rum raisins, or vanilla pods','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-06-01'),(190,'AB:11','Black Barley Wine With Ginger, Raspberries, Chipotle Peppers.','08/2012','AB:11 is an Imperial Black Barley Wine brewed with ginger, black raspberries and chipotle peppers. A 12.8% rollercoaster of ginger zestiness and chipotle smokiness, all bound together with dark berry tartness and the decadent residual body of a Black Barley Wine.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/189.png',12.8,70,1020,1108,79,40,4.4,81.5,20,25,18,'Grated ginger root: 62.5g for 45mins, Add chipotle peppers and raspberries into the FV post- fermentation, Chipotle','Grated ginger root: 62.5g for 45mins, Add chipotle peppers and raspberries into the FV post- fermentation, Chipotle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-08-01'),(191,'Hello My Name is Sonja (w/ Evil Twin)','Blueberry Double IPA.','09/2013','Brewed in collaboration with Jeppe from Evil Twin Brewing (and named after his mum), this Double IPA is big on fruity Flavours. Single hopped with Mosaic for lots of tropical, passion fruit and citrus Flavours. Loaded with well over 100kg of blueberries, the original was one super fruity hop bomb.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/190.png',8.3,70,1013,1076,30,15,4.4,82.9,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',6,'2013-09-01'),(192,'Interstellar','2013 Prototype Red Rye IPA.','11/2013','Interstellar is a Red Rye IPA with spicy rye Flavours from the malt and with great all-round spicy, fruity and earthy hop aromas from the use of Willamette and Amarillo.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/191.png',6.5,55,1011,1059,50,25,4.4,81.4,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-11-01'),(193,'Punk IPA 2007 - 2010','Post Modern Classic. Spiky. Tropical. Hoppy.','04/2007','Our flagship beer that kick started the craft beer revolution. This is James and Martin\'s original take on an American IPA, subverted with punchy New Zealand hops. Layered with new world hops to create an all-out riot of grapefruit, pineapple and lychee before a spiky, mouth-puckering bitter finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/192.png',6,60,1010,1056,17,8.5,4.4,82.14,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2007-04-01'),(194,'Blitz Berliner Weisse','Berliner Fruit Beer.','07/2013','Our sour recipe for all fruit Blitz beers uses a process called kettle souring. In this we steep a bag of malt in the wort to allow the bacteria to grow in it.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3,8,1040,1007,9,4.5,3.2,82.5,20,25,19,'Before main fermentation steep a bag of malt in the wort for 48 hours. Re boil the wort before pitching in the yeast for the main fermentation.','Before main fermentation steep a bag of malt in the wort for 48 hours. Re boil the wort before pitching in the yeast for the main fermentation.','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-07-01'),(195,'Hardkogt IPA','A Special Double IPA For Our Danish Friends.','06/2010','Brewed for the beer maniacs in Denmark, this Double IPA quivered with kumquat, kiwi and orange pith all held together with a honeycomb malt body.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/194.png',7.6,175,1014,1072,40,20,4.4,80.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2010-06-01'),(196,'Hello My Name Is Holy Moose','Nordic Berry IPA.','07/2015','Cloudberry, lingonberry, blueberry and sea buckthorn meld with citrusy hops in an intensely sweet, fruity and floral aroma, with toasty malt notes and tropical fruit bursts. This bitter, resinous IPA follows up with a lemony punch in the mouth - cherry and blueberry sourness takes this pithy pale ale in a new direction before a long, dry finish.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/195.png',5.5,35,1011,1053,25,12.5,4.4,79.3,20,25,17,'Lingon Berries: 25g at end, Cloudberries: 25g ate end, Blueberry Concentrate: 62.5g at FV, Sea Buckthorn: 62.5g at FV','Lingon Berries: 25g at end, Cloudberries: 25g ate end, Blueberry Concentrate: 62.5g at FV, Sea Buckthorn: 62.5g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-07-01'),(197,'Catherine\'s Pony (w/ Beavertown)','Imperial Smoked Porter – Beavertown Collab.','12/2012','An Imperial Smoked Porter with a nose like gooseberries and blueberries, stuffed with coffee, covered in chocolate and toasted on a campfire by the beach, Catherine’s Pony is robust and imposing with a herculean mouthfeel. Rich and smooth with roasted smoky Flavours battling for prominence over the assertive bitterness. A satisfying hoppiness rounds off the palate.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/196.png',8.8,40,1017,1084,190,95,4.5,79.8,20,25,21,'Coffee at end for Flavour','Coffee at end for Flavour','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-12-01'),(198,'Moshi Moshi 15','American Pale Ale Birthday Beer.','11/2013','A riot of C-hops, with layers of grapefruit, lime zest, pine needles, freshly cut grass, pungent resin, layered up on toasty malt with a touch of caramel sweetness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/197.png',5.2,45,1011,1048,35,17.5,4.4,77.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-11-01'),(199,'AB:01','Vanilla Bean Infused Belgian Quad.','02/2010','Made with the yeast from a bottle of Westvleteren 12, aged with vanilla beans. Only available in 375ml bottles. Limited to 3200 bottles. The first in our Abstrakt series.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/198.png',10.2,20,1018,1095,16,8,4.1,8.1,20,25,22,'Two split vanilla pods in cold conditioning','Two split vanilla pods in cold conditioning','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',19,'2010-02-01'),(200,'Alice Porter','Enigmatic Dark Alchemy.','09/2010','First brewed in 2010, Alice Porter returned as a seasonal in 2015. The beer was originally created and brewed for (real life) Alice Porter’s impending nuptials to the Beer King of Leeds, Matt Gorecki.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/199.png',5.2,55,1013,1053,165,82.5,5.2,75.5,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2010-09-01'),(201,'Double IPA - Russian Doll','Nesting Hop Bomb.','08/2014','The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected Flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/200.png',8,85,1013,1074,35,17.5,5.2,82.4,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-08-01'),(202,'Waimea - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2013','Waimea has a new world Flavour, infusing unique fresh crushed citrus aroma and Flavour notes into this IPA - think intense fresh tangelo, citrus fruit and pine needle characteristics. There is a huge depth of Flavour with astringent gooseberry balanced against the robust malt base.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/201.png',6.7,70,1015,1066,30,15,4.4,77.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2013-02-01'),(203,'Dog C','Cacao, Coffee Chili Anniversary Stout.','05/2014','Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn\'t change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental stout.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/202.png',15,90,1003,1120,100,50,4.4,98,20,25,19,'Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.','Based on AB:04, but with added vanilla and 3.5 times the chilli.','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-05-01'),(204,'Bitch Please (w/ 3 Floyds)','Barley Wine - 3 Floyds Collab.','02/2012','This limited edition American Barley Wine was brewed in collaboration with 3 Floyds Brewery. This beer had all the warm, boozy and smoky aspects of an Islay Scotch whisky with the sweet malt and devastatingly bitter attributes of a barley wine. Peat smoke features prominently, backed up with a complex fruity hop profile.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/203.png',11.5,50,1016,1104,38,19,4.4,85,20,25,21,'Two bars of Highland Toffee at start of boil','Two bars of Highland Toffee at start of boil','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2012-02-01'),(205,'Cascade, Centennial & Willamette IPA - B-Sides','Pilot Kit IPA.','01/2016','An experiment in balancing hops on the pilot kit. Grapefruit, orange and resin to the fore.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.4,65,1011,1060,14,7,5.2,82,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',16,'2016-01-01'),(206,'Shareholder Black IPA 2011','Shareholder Black IPA.','12/2011','Brewed as part of the shareholder brewday at our Fraserburgh brewery. Massively dry hopped and aged on toasted oak chips, this IPA was a riot of lemon, vanilla and roasted malt.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.1,80,1014,1067,71,36,4.4,79,20,25,19,'Several dozen brewers!, Toasted oak chips: 75g at FV','Several dozen brewers!, Toasted oak chips: 75g at FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2011-12-01'),(207,'Black Jacques','Red Wine Barrel-Aged Imperial Black Saison.','06/2013','A Black Saison, brewed with oats and wheat for a silky mouthfeel, Spicy hops and Carafa Malt for colour, then aged in red wine barrels. On the nose there\'s cola, chocolate, coffee, mint humbug, warming oak, and spice. The myriad Flavours touch on treacle, ripe banana, espresso, brandy, and a clean herbal warmth.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/206.png',11.1,45,1005,1089,15,7.5,4.4,94.4,20,25,23,'Grains of paradise: 10g at End (WP), Lemon Peel: 25g at End (WP), Ginger: 7.5g at End (WP)','Grains of paradise: 10g at End (WP), Lemon Peel: 25g at End (WP), Ginger: 7.5g at End (WP)','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',3,'2013-06-01'),(208,'International Arms Race (w/ Flying Dog)','Zero IBU Herbal IPA.','08/2012','The International Arms Race was a new type of battle collaboration between hardcore American craft brewery Flying Dog and BrewDog. Both breweries attempted to brew an IPA with absolutely no hops.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/207.png',7.5,0,1013,1069,50,25,4.4,81.1,20,25,19,'Juniper Berries: 25g at start, Bay Leaves: 2.75g at start, Rosemary: 7.5g at start, Rosemary: 5g at end, Elderflower: 15g at end, Juniper Berries: 25g at end','Juniper Berries: 25g at start, Bay Leaves: 2.75g at start, Rosemary: 7.5g at start, Rosemary: 5g at end, Elderflower: 15g at end, Juniper Berries: 25g at end','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2012-08-01'),(209,'Sunshine On Rye - B-Sides','Hoppy Rye IPA.','02/2015','A Pilot Brew \"Sunshine on Rye\" uses loads of spicy malt and coriander to play nice with an inhuman amount of hops!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.2,130,1010,1065,14,7,5.2,87,20,25,20,'Indian Coriander: 2.5g','Indian Coriander: 2.5g','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-02-01'),(210,'Stereo Wolf Stout - Prototype Challenge','Dark Audio Storm.','02/2015','Roasty, dark and complex, Stereo Wolf is a 5.2% ABV Stout brewed with a cacophony of hop-driven fruit and spice. Dark chocolate stalks alongside the resonating bitterness, through to Stereo Wolf’s lingering dry finish. Balancing roasty malt and new world hops at 5.2% ABV is no mean feat, but Stereo Wolf takes it in its stride.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/209.png',5.2,55,1014,1052,200,100,5.2,73.1,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2015-02-01'),(211,'Dead Metaphor','Scottish Breakfast Stout.','09/2013','Scottish chocolate breakfast Stout - brewed with Brazilian Sertão coffee, Venezuelan cacao and (for the Scottish element) oatmeal. Smooth, chocolately and rich, with a honeycomb mouthfeel and a rich red berry coffee character. Brewed with our beer blogger friends from The Beer Cast and Hopzine.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/210.png',6.8,30,1016,1068,86,43,4.4,76.5,20,25,19,'Cacao: 37.5g at end, Lactose: 125g at end, Ground Coffee: 6.3g at end.','Cacao: 37.5g at end, Lactose: 125g at end, Ground Coffee: 6.3g at end.','Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-09-01'),(212,'Black Dog','Hoppy Black Wheat Stout.','11/2009','We thought it would be great if Jeremy Moynier from Stone Brewing Co. brewed his own beer while he was here, with Jeremy deciding everything right down to the name! The result is a special 20HL batch of BlackDog, a 5.5% dark wheat stout with Columbus, Simcoe and Chinook and of course plenty of dry hopping action.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.5,60,1020,1062,230,115,4.4,67.7,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Phil Nash <philnash>',1,'2009-11-01'),(213,'Hop Fiction - Prototype Challenge','US-Style Pale Ale.','11/2014','Hop Fiction is an explosively tropical US-style Pale Ale. We rolled up our hop-dusted sleeves and put some advanced brewing techniques to work on this seasonal brew. Hop Fiction’s incredible aromas and Flavours are down to a combination of early and late hops. Bags of soft, rounded citrus and stone fruit layer up on a dry light biscuit backbone. Hop Fiction, beer fact.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/212.png',5.2,40,1010,1048,13,6.5,4.4,79.2,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2014-11-01'),(214,'El Dorado - IPA Is Dead','Single Hop India Pale Ale.','02/2013','The Pacific North West of America grows remarkable hops and El Dorado is a killer example of this. A new hop on the block, loaded with tropical fruits, pear, watermelon, candy floss and stone fruit.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/213.png',6.7,70,1015,1066,30,15,4.4,77.3,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2013-02-01'),(215,'Cult Lager','US & New Zeland Hopped Lager','04/2008','A lager that actually tastes of something? You have to be kidding, right? Cult lager is made with 100% malt and whole leaf hops. Maybe we are crazy, so what? Taste our lager and we are pretty sure that you will agree that the fine line between insanity and genius has just become a little more blurred.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/214.png',5.4,50,1049,1008,19,8,4.1,83.7,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',5,'2008-04-01'),(216,'Brixton Porter','Paradigm-Changing Porter.','11/2013','Brixton Porter delivers bold chocolate and coffee Flavours with light smokiness and hints of autumn fruit all but built on a low ABV, lighter bodied backbone. Complex and intriguing, with spicy bitterness, but very sessionable.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/215.png',5,50,1014,1053,200,100,4.4,73.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Ali Skinner <AliSkinner>',1,'2013-11-01'),(217,'Barrel Aged Hinterland','A Most Beguiling Brew. Aged In Bourbon Casks.','06/2016','Hinterland is a beer long in the creation, and even longer in the appreciation. On the aroma, deep reverberating roasty bitterness and sweet dark chocolate. Also in evidence, woodsmoke, rich vanilla, mocha and marzipan. When tasting, Hinterland reveals itself as the beer moves from cellar temperature to something warmer, yielding all of the above plus dried fruit, rich ganache and ending on a resoundingly warming  nish redolent of chocolate liqueur or plum brandy. Aged in Bourbon Casks.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/216.png',9,85,1025,1094,400,200,4.3,73.4,20,25,21,'Lactose (Milk Sugar): 500g at middle','Lactose (Milk Sugar): 500g at middle','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(218,'Barrel Aged Albino Squid Assassin','Red Rye IPA Aged In Rye Whisky Cask.','06/2016','This tentacled terminator packs a punch - ten punches to be precise. Each hop addition adds to the intense layers of depth in this red rye IPA. Toasty caramel & cinder toffee from crystal malts, cacao richness from intensely roasted malt and the spiciness of rye. Zesty pithiness from Citra and the robust resin of Chinook. This small batch exclusive brew is up-front intensity matched with twisted complexity. Aged in Rye Whisky Casks.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/217.png',9.2,65,1012,1069,60,30,4.2,82.6,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2016-06-01'),(219,'Monk Hammer','Our Ruthless IPA With A Belgian Twist.','03/2016','Jack Hammer has been single handedly ripping it up for quite some time. Now, the definitive bitter and twisted IPA, has spawned four Hammer Head off-springs. Monk Hammer is the first of our super-charge hyped up hybrids. A dark cloaked holy man packing an unholy punch. Belgian yeast and American hops untie on a cardinal scale. Steel yourself for biblical volumes of grapefruit, bow your head for a wave of spicy, fruity yeast character, then cross yourself for the bitterest of bitter finishes. Let your senses succumb to this 21st century incarnation. Monk Hammer – worship daily.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/218.png',7.2,250,1010,1065,15,7.5,4.4,84.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',4,'2016-03-01'),(220,'Ship Wreck','Redacted Collaboration Ale.','03/2016','This mezcal-inspired brew is the shipwrecked remains of a collaboration brewed with former craft brewers Ballast Point. Brewed to encapsulate the Flavours of mezcal, this beer smoulders with peaty and light woody notes, as well as intense fruity character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/219.png',13.8,60,1015,1088,25,13,4.4,83,20,25,21,'100g Oak chips soaked in Mezcal and 1.6kg Agave syrup in FV','100g Oak chips soaked in Mezcal and 1.6kg Agave syrup in FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-03-01'),(221,'Ace Of Simcoe','Single-Hopped Session IPA.','01/2016','We love hops. We adore and worship their profile ability to transform beer. You could say that we have a terminal addiction. To celebrate this fetish we’re heroing our favourites in single hopped limited releases. No also starring, no extras, no compromise. The Hop is the Hero. A biscuity malty backbone builds to resinous pine with explosive citrus notes, culminating in a mango hit and a long bitter finish. This is pure Hop fusion, imploding with sensory overload. Our Ace in the hole, devastatingly singular, deliciously bitter. Serving up an Ace each and every time.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/220.png',4.5,40,1011,1045,18,9,4.2,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2016-01-01'),(222,'Blitz Series','Fruit Infused Berlinerweisse.','06/2016','We are bringing back our Blitz Series to 2016. Every Blitz we brew is different, due to the spontaneous souring process, and each version has a great blend of all the different Flavours we look for in a Berlinerwiesse.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.2,8,1032,1007,8,3,3.2,78,20,25,21,'Conversion check 78°C run off.','Conversion check 78°C run off.','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',1,'2016-06-01'),(223,'Dog E','Ninth Anniversary Imperial Stout.','06/2016','Dog E is a very special beer. This beer commemorates our 9th year in 2016. This beer originally appeared as AB:04 in 2010, perhaps the most sought after beer we ever brewed. Dog E is a 16.1% Imperial Stout brewed with copious amounts of dark malts, pure cacao and coffee, balanced by the subtle addition of naga chili, and barrel-aged. Perfect for ageing in your cellar, or drinking fresh if you’re lucky enough to get your paws on a bottle.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/222.png',16.1,100,1125,1015,500,254,4.4,84,20,25,21,'5g Habanero and 3g lemon drop chili in FV','5g Habanero and 3g lemon drop chili in FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(224,'Prototype Pils 2.0','Revamped German Pils.','06/2016','Our spin on a light, dry and bitter German lager. Hop driven with malt taking a back seat, Pils 2.0 is lined up to become a regular brew.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.7,25,1044,1008,25,5,4.2,75.6,20,25,12,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2016-06-01'),(225,'AB:20','Tiramisu Barley Wine.','06/2016','An English Barley Wine brewed with coffee and milk, with rich toasty & caramel Flavours. To complete the tiramisu effect, we’ve blended this with a 3 year rum cask aged Imperial Stout.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/224.png',14.2,20,1120,1025,67,34,4,75.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(226,'Paradox Islay 2.0','Islay Cask-Aged Imperial Stout.','06/2016','Intense peaty smoke layers on decadent roast coffee and chocolate in our Islay barrels aged paradox stout. One of the smokiest beers we have ever produced.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/225.png',13,100,1112,1015,300,152,4.4,84.4,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(227,'Chili Hammer','Our Ruthless IPA With A Fiery Twist.','06/2016','Chili Hammer is the third of our super-charged hyped up hybrids. A smooth tongued spicy assassin. Chili and American hops unite for a Flavour bigger than Texas. Citrus peel, mango, with a hint of spice on the nose. Delivers big grapefruit and mango with a smooth chili kick, followed by the bitterest of bitter finishes. Chili Hammer – turn up the gas.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/226.png',7.2,250,1010,1065,15,7.5,4.4,84.6,20,25,21,'2.5g chili powder in the boil, 1 whole chili in FV','2.5g chili powder in the boil, 1 whole chili in FV','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(228,'Brewdog Vs Beavertown','Coffee And Cigarettes.','06/2016','Loaded with roasty coffee notes and balanced with complex tobacco character. With smoky Flavours from the malt, our Beavertown Collab is barrel-aged, but we don’t know for how long until its ready!','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/227.png',9.2,50,1085,1016,78.8,40,4.2,81,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(229,'Prototype Helles','Laid-Back Bavarian Classic.','06/2016','Our spin on one-of the most popular beer styles ever conceived. A celebration of light, bready malt, with toasty hints and soft bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.9,18,1047,1010,13,6.6,4.2,78.7,20,25,12,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',2,'2016-06-01'),(230,'Rye Hammer','Our Ruthless IPA with A Spicy Twist.','06/2016','Rye Hammer is the fourth of our super-charged hyped up hybrids. A bready beery beast. Rye grains and American hops unite in an agricultural superpower. Aroma of roasted malts, rye bread and subtle floral hops. Grapefruit, roasted caramel with malty fruity notes, followed by the bitterest of bitter finishes. Rye Hammer – liquid daily bread.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/229.png',7.2,250,1010,1065,17,8.5,4.4,84.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(231,'Black Hammer','Our Ruthless IPA With A Dark Malt Twist.','06/2016','Jack Hammer has been single handedly ripping it up for quite some time. Now, the definitive bitter and twisted IPA, has spawned four Hammer Head off-springs. Black Hammer is the second of our hyped up hybrid IPAs. A black hearted beast, that takes no prisoners. American hops and dark malt combine to make mischief. Grapefruit and coffee collide in sensory overload – a wake-up call for other IPA’s. Molten waves of pithy grapefruit build and finally ebb to the roasty bitter onslaught. Stand  firm and wield the Black Hammer with care. Stare into the black abyss and succumb to the dark-side.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/230.png',7.2,250,1010,1065,104,53,4.4,84.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-06-01'),(232,'Ace Of Chinook','Single-Hopped Session IPA.','01/2016','We love hops. We adore and worship their profile ability to transform beer. You could say that we have a terminal addiction. To celebrate this fetish we’re heroing our favourites in single hopped limited releases. No also starring, no extras, no compromise. The Hop is the Hero. A biscuity malty backbone builds to intense resinous pine with pithy citrus notes, culminating in a grapefruit hit and a long bitter finish. Our Ace in the hole, devastatingly singular, deliciously bitter. Serving up an Ace each and every time.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/231.png',4.5,40,1011,1045,18,9,4.2,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2016-01-01'),(233,'Ace Of Equinox','Single-Hopped Session IPA.','01/2016','We love hops. We adore and worship their profile ability to transform beer. You could say that we have a terminal addiction. To celebrate this fetish we’re heroing our favourites in single hopped limited releases. No also starring, no extras, no compromise. The Hop is the Hero. A biscuity malty backbone builds to intense tropical fruit, with bitter resin notes, culminating with an explosive papya hit and a long bitter finish. Our Ace in the hole, devastatingly singular, deliciously bitter. Serving up an Ace each and every time.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/232.png',4.5,40,1011,1045,18,9,4.2,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2016-01-01'),(234,'Ace Of Citra','Single-Hopped Session IPA.','01/2016','We love hops. We adore and worship their profile ability to transform beer. You could say that we have a terminal addiction. To celebrate this fetish we’re heroing our favourites in single hopped limited releases. No also starring, no extras, no compromise. The Hop is the Hero. A biscuity malty backbone layered with berry and resin, culminating with a lime zest hit and an explosive bitter citrus finish. Our Ace in the hole, devastatingly singular, deliciously bitter. Serving up an Ace each and every time.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/233.png',4.5,40,1011,1045,18,9,4.2,75.6,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',1,'2016-01-01'),(235,'Neon Overlord','Mango And Chilli IPA','01/2016','The Overlord of mango and chili IPA’s packs a fruity punch and then some. Pours a slightly hazy orange. A tropical fruit assault on the nose, with mango, pineapple, apricots and citrus. Hints of chili and sweet malts follow. Fruit dissipates to a chili kick, not hot but definitely there, followed by a long bitter finish. All hail to the hot tempered sweet toothed Lord.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/234.png',7.6,70,1012,1067,20,10,4.4,82,20,25,21,'250g mango puree in FV','250g mango puree in FV','Matt Ball <GeordieMatt>',6,'2016-01-01'),(236,'Mango And Chili Barley Wine','Spicy Chewy Sweet','2016','A huge, chewy barley wine, loaded with bitterness and balanced with a sweet and spicy combo of mango and chili. A concept brew which was so well received, we tweaked it and it became Neon Overlord.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',12,NULL,1015,1110,20,40,4.4,84,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-01-01'),(237,'Science IPA','India Pale Ale','2016','A beer brewed specifically for the British Science Festival, held in Swansea.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5,NULL,1011,1050,24,47,4.4,77,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-01-01'),(238,'Honey And Lemon Blitz','Honey & Lemon Infused Berliner Weisse.','2016','Honey & Lemon Blitz sees tart Berliner Weisse character multiplied by lemony acidity; light bready malt and a hint of warming honey hold this back from the brink of palate- destroying sourness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.2,NULL,1008,1039,8,4,3.2,75,20,25,21,'Following souring steps outlined in Blitz Series recipes','Following souring steps outlined in Blitz Series recipes','Sam Mason <samjbmason>',6,'2016-01-01'),(239,'Kingpin','21st century lager.','2016','A 4.7% German Pils with light, biscuit and toasty malt character, upon which is built a hop bitterness that provides complexity and a long, dry finish.',NULL,4.7,40,1008,1044,14,7,4.2,79,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',2,'2016-01-01'),(240,'#Mashtag 2016','Sour cherry triple IPA.','2016','We gave our customers the keys to the brewery and let them choose every aspect of this beer. Sour cherry combines with fruity hop character against a biscuit malt backbone with a hint of alcohol warmth, and an oaky undercurrent.',NULL,10.5,100,1010,1090,15,8,4.4,89.04,20,25,21,'250g Sour Cherries, 5g Oak Chips','250g Sour Cherries, 5g Oak Chips','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(241,'Blitz Saison','Lemon & coriander Berliner Weisse','2016','Belgium meets Berlin – incredible saison character with a bright and vibrant sour edge.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.2,8,1007,1040,7,14,3.2,77,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',3,'2016-01-01'),(242,'Hello My Name Is Ingrid 2016','Cloudberry Double IPA','2016','We asked the public to tell us the one beer we should brew again, from our entire back catalogue. They chose well. Cloudberries team up with pan-global hops for an all out fruit riot against a caramel malt base.',NULL,8.2,70,1013,1076,30,15.2,5.2,83.3,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(243,'Crew Brew','Democratic Amber Ale','2016','Our crew designed it, and we bottled it just for ourselves! We chose an 8% red ale, mash hopped and first wort hopped with New Zealand origin hops.',NULL,8,100,1011,1072,28,14.2,5.2,84.62,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(244,'Gin Blitz','Botanical Berliner Weisse','2016','Our Blitz series sees us brew up low abv, super tart Berliner Weisse, and generally infuse them with bags of sour fruit Flavour – but this batch uses gin botanicals instead.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',3.2,8,1008,1038,8,4,3.2,75,20,25,21,'Kettle Soured','Kettle Soured','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2016-01-01'),(245,'AB:21','Liquorice Blackcurrant Stout.','2016','AB:21 is a liquorice and blackcurrant infused imperial stout. Rolling in at an imposing 12% abv, this huge and decadent dark beer dials down the charred roastiness and focuses instead on the rich, full-bodied chocolate and dark fruit character of the style.',NULL,12,100,1015,1130,200,101.6,5.1,82,20,25,19,'Liquorice and 200g Blackcurrant Concentrate FV.','Liquorice and 200g Blackcurrant Concentrate FV.','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(246,'Beatnik','Imperial Red Ale','2016','We gave our Equity Punks the keys to the brewery and let them brew the beer, as well as join Q&As and tour our HQ. The beer was voted on exclusively by Equity Punks.',NULL,8,60,1013,1075,60,30.5,5.2,83.78,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(247,'Casino Rye Ale','Life\'s a Gamble','2016','We’ve split our bets with Casino Rye Ale and doubled up on the malt front, with barley and rye on the grain bill.',NULL,5.1,40,1009,1049,25,12.7,5.2,81.6,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2016-01-01'),(248,'Self Assembly Pope','Coconut Vanilla Porter','2016','A dark and decadent beer brewed with coconut, vanilla, cacao.',NULL,7.4,75,1016,1072,200,101.6,5.1,82,20,25,19,'Toasted Coconut Chips – 40g FV & Vanilla Extract – FV','Toasted Coconut Chips – 40g FV & Vanilla Extract – FV','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(249,'Twin Atlantic','Mango & Pineapple Pale','2016','Brewed in collaboration with our AGM-headlining band, Twin Atlantic, this US style pale features some of our favourite hops and is loaded with tropical fruit.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5,80,1011,1048,19,9.7,5.2,77,20,25,19,'Mango and Pineapple added to FV after Primary fermentation','Mango and Pineapple added to FV after Primary fermentation','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2016-01-01'),(250,'Hop Shot','Quadruple India Pale Ale','2016','Hop Shot is a high-velocity hop hit. Our latest experiment in ice-distillation is a west coast IPA, subjected to Antarctic temperatures and concentrated by removing the ice that forms. The result is a 22% ABV hop grenade in a 110ml bottle.',NULL,7,250,1010,1065,15,7.5,4.4,85,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(251,'Small Batch: Rye IPA','Rye India Pale Ale.','2016','A 7.2% rye IPA loaded with grapefruit notes, pithy citrus, and huge resinous bitterness, with rye character. The Centennial and Columbus Flavours are amplified by the spicy, dry rye.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.2,100,1010,1065,8,16,4.4,84,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(252,'Small Batch: Sorachi Ace Session','Sorachi Ace Belgian Pale.','2016','This brew is a pale ale fermented with Belgian yeast and spiced with coriander seed.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4,25,1005,1035,15,7.62,5.1,79,20,25,19,'Crushed Coridaner Seeds – FV','Crushed Coridaner Seeds – FV','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',20,'2016-01-01'),(253,'Small Batch: Dortmunder','Pale Lager.','2017','A pale lager, with toasty biscuit malt balanced against a robust spicy bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.9,32,1009,1049,15,7.62,5.2,81.5,20,25,14,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',21,'2017-01-01'),(254,'Small Batch: 90 Shilling','Honeyed Spicy Malt.','2017','A malt-forward Scotch ale with a complex but mellow mix of toast crust, caramel, hints of cocoa, and a light hop spiciness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.3,25,1010,1056,40,20.32,4.2,73,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(255,'Small Batch: Kellerbier','Crisp Unfiltered Goodness.','2017','A pale lager, with toasty biscuit malt balances against a robust spicy bitterness.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.5,25,1011,1043,17,8.6,5.3,79,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',21,'2017-01-01'),(256,'Small Batch: Tripel','Spiced Belgium Ale.','2017','Intense spicy and citrusy notes backed up with a bitter edge and a warming but dry malt biscuit backbone. This beer comes into its own after cellaring cool for a few weeks.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',13,50,1008,1110,23,11.6,5.1,93,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',20,'2017-01-01'),(257,'Small Batch: Vermont IPA','Juicy, Tropical, Citrusy.','2017','A vermont style IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with intense juicy fruit character.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.9,35,1012,1066,15,7.62,4.2,79,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(258,'Semi Skimmed Occultist','Oatmeal Milk Stout.','2017','This one-off brew is packed with all the decadent Flavours and textures associated with Imperial Stouts. This can features exclusive artwork by The Red Dress.',NULL,8,70,1014,1080,160,81.28,4.1,73,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(259,'Paradox Rye','Rye Whisky Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout.','2005','In 2006 James and Martin hijacked a beer dinner run by Michael Jackson, the acclaimed beer and whisky writer, and convinced him to taste one of their home brews. This was a defining moment in BrewDog prehistory, and that beer was the first incarnation of the ubiquitous Paradox. Aged in a variety of casks over the years, Paradox is dark, decadent and encapsulating. Can be enjoyed fresh; phenomenal when aged.',NULL,13,100,1015,1112,300,152,4.4,84,20,25,21,'Age this beer in Rye Whisky Casks.','Age this beer in Rye Whisky Casks.','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2005-01-01'),(260,'Tropic Thunder','Island-Hopping Stout.','2016','Tropic Thunder is the winner of the first ever #HomeBrewDog competition; the brainchild of Tom Doyle, this beer was the highest rated of the 307 beers that were tasted. A full-bodied and complex stout loaded with chocolate, mocha and roasty Flavours, finishing with a vibrant burst of orange.',NULL,7,25,1020,1074,170,86.36,4.2,73,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2016-01-01'),(261,'New England IPA','Vermont IPA','2017','BrewDog vs Cloudwater is a 6.8% Vermont-style India Pale Ale, hopped with Mosaic in the whirlpool only. Without any big- hitting additions of hops in the boil, we carried the Flavour by heavily dry-hopping the brew with Citra and Mosaic. We also used oats in the recipe to deliver the trademark smooth mouthfeel – and made it truly authentic by propagating a one-off culture of Vermont yeast, specifically for the brew.',NULL,6.8,45,1012,1065,17,9,4.2,79,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',22,'2017-01-01'),(262,'Small Batch: Nitro Breakfast Stout','Boozy Chocolate Milkshake.','2017','An utterly indulgent, smooth as hell Stout. With opulent Flavours of chocolate milkshake, roasty espresso coffee, and mellow vanilla, this beer has a full-bodied and creamy mouthfeel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',8,80,1027,1092,88,44.7,5.2,70,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(263,'Small Batch: Vermont IPA V2.0','Juicy, Citrusy, Tropical.','2017','A second trial of our previous Small Batch Vermont IPA using a different yeast strain. A vermont style IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with intense juicy fruit characters.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.9,35,1012,1066,15,7.6,4.2,79,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',22,'2017-01-01'),(264,'Small Batch: Mandarina Lager','Pithy Pale Pilsner.','2017','A bitter pils-style lager which is packed with aromas of citrus and a dry, refreshing biscuit malt backbone. Light floral notes add to the complexity.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.3,40,1008,1049,7,4,4.3,84,20,25,10,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',23,'2017-01-01'),(265,'Small Batch: East Coast Crush','Session Vermont IPA.','2017','East Coast Crush is a Vermont style pale ale, packaged and served using our custom LIVE beer dispense. A session Vermont IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with intense juicy mango, pineapple, peach and pine.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',4.8,25,1010,1047,15,8,4.2,79,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(266,'Pump Action Poet','Stone Fruit IPA.','2017','A one-off beer which combines the sweet and juicy Flavour of stonefruit with tropical hop aromas. This can features exclusive artwork by Tracie Ching.',NULL,7.5,40,1013,1070,12,6,5.2,81,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(267,'Small Batch: Lemon Meringue Pie','Experimental Dessert Beer.','2017','Brewed to a concept voted on at Craft Beer Rising, this one-off beer is an experimental brew which emulates the Flavour of lemon meringue pie.',NULL,6.5,5,1015,1066,7,4,4,77,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(268,'AB:22','Speyside Barrel-Aged Coffee Chocolate Stout.','2017','An imperial stout brewed with cacao and coffee, AB22 has spent two years in darkness, drawing complex and indulgent Flavours from the Speyside whisky casks in which it resided.',NULL,12.5,70,1020,1115,100,51,4.1,83,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(269,'Hazy Jane','New England IPA.','2017','A Vermont style IPA, with low background bitterness, loaded with juicy fruit character. Pine, stonefruit, mango, light resin and hints of lime peel - this juicy IPA is low in bitterness, full-bodied and smooth, enhancing the soft ripe fruit Flavours.',NULL,7.2,30,1009,1065,15,8,4.2,86,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(270,'Small Batch: Imperial Pale Weizen','Dry-Hopped Wheat Beer.','2017','An amplified version of a style we first brewed with Weihenstephan. A full-on deluge of spice and citrus, the new world hops bring spiced orange, lemon peel and fresh grassy and floral notes while the weizen base adds pepper, clove and banana.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',7.5,25,1010,1067,18,9,4.4,85,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',14,'2017-01-01'),(271,'Blonde Export Stout','Beatnik Brewing Collective 2017.','2017','Our Equity Punk gypsy brewery - Beatnik Brewing Collective - voted for this recipe as their 2017 annual brew. A blonde stout brewed to export strength, the stout character comes from extra ingredients instead of dark malts.',NULL,7,55,1020,1075,16,8,4.4,73,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(272,'Small Batch: Cranachan Cream Ale','Raspberry Cream Ale.','2017','A cream ale, brewed with raspberry and milk sugars, balancing sweet and tart summer berry with soft bitterness and a full bodied smooth mouthfeel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',6.5,8,1019,1069,10,5,4.3,72,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(273,'Small Batch: Spelt & Honey Saison','Honey & Spelt Saison','2017','A pilot kit Small Batch, experimenting with weizen yeast, honey and spelt.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.2,22,1008,1046,8,4,4.1,83,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',14,'2017-01-01'),(274,'Prototype Double IPA','American Hop Overload.','2017','Our Prototype Challenge sees us pit three new trial beers against each other. This Double IPA is packed with a blend of our favourite American hops and has a huge dry- hop aroma.',NULL,8.5,60,1007,1073,15,8,4.2,90,20,25,18,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(275,'Prototype Black Rye IPA','Complex Dark Ale','2017','Our Prototype Challenge sees us pit three new trial beers against each other. This Black Rye IPA combines two spins on an American IPA, in the left-right jab combo of extra ingredients.',NULL,6.5,70,1012,1060,135,69,4.5,80,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(276,'Sidewalk Shark','Citrus-Infused German Sour.','2017','A citrus-infused gose - a traditional German sour wheat beer brewed with salt, in this case with the addition of kaffir lime leaf and lemon peel.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.2,22,1008,1055,7,4,3.8,85,20,25,20,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(277,'Nine To Five Wizard','India Pale Weizen.','2017','A classic German weissbeir with aromas of banana and clove, layered with New World hop aromas of orange.',NULL,7.5,35,1012,1069,20,10,4.3,83,20,25,24,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',8,'2017-01-01'),(278,'Prototype Blonde Ale','Mellow Golden Ale.','2017','This Blonde Ale is a new recipe and uses a new yeast - so it is a true Prototype. Originally lined up as part of the 2017 Prototype Challenge it was released shortly afterwards. but hey, these things happen.',NULL,4.5,15,1009,1044,12,6,4.6,80,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',24,'2017-01-01'),(279,'AB:23','Bourbon Barrel-Aged Barley Wine.','2017','Our Abstrakt series showcases one-off beers, brewed or blended to the peak of our abilities. Each release is unique and never to be repeated.',NULL,11.5,80,1020,1110,80,41,4.1,82,20,25,21,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(280,'Slot Machine','Red Rye IPA.','2017','Our Q4 Seasonal is a red rye IPA. This twist on an American IPA involves a more complex malt base, with the careful addition of rye - a grain known for its trickiness when brewing with anything above a tiny percentage.',NULL,5.2,50,1011,1051,50,25,4.3,78,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',1,'2017-01-01'),(281,'Make Earth Great Again','Cloudberry Saison.','2017','In protest against the potential withdrawal of the USA from the Paris agreement, we brewed a saison (which ferments at high temperatures) with melted ice caps (glacier water) and cloudberries (an Arctic berry).',NULL,7.5,35,1004,1065,9,5,4.6,94,20,25,23,'10kg of glacier water added to the mash.','10kg of glacier water added to the mash.','John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',3,'2017-01-01'),(282,'Homicidal Puppet Help Desk','Barrel-Aged Rye Barley Wine.','2017','Indulgent, complex, and endlessly rewarding; packed with Flavours of toffee, coconut, red berry, burnt sugar, marzipan, orange, cherry - American oak adds structure and depth to this chewy and warming barley wine brewed with rye and aged in rye whiskey cask.',NULL,11.5,132,1020,1105,45,23,4.1,81,20,25,19,NULL,NULL,'John Jenkman <johnjenkman>',6,'2017-01-01'),(283,'Pina Colada Sidewalk','Pineapple & Coconut Gose.','2017','After the success of the first version of Sidewalk Shark (a BrewDog bar exclusive), we decided to brew a second version, this time infused with tropical Flavours of pineapple, coconut and lime.','https://images.punkapi.com/v2/keg.png',5.2,